While there, Dr. Lenington continued to excel, being selected as the chief resident of the surgery department.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: Dr. Linares has been in practice in the Denver area since 2000. She completed medical school at Howard University College of Medicine in Washington, D.C. followed by a family medicine residency program affiliated with Mount Sinai Medical School in New York City. She is Board Certified in Family Medicine and has completed the AAFP course in Advanced Life Support in Obstetrics and Advanced Cardiac Life Support. She is currently serving her second term as Chief of Family Medicine at Sky Ridge Medical Center. Dr. Linares enjoys obstetrics as part of her professional interests. Most of her patients receive their obstetrical care as well as their other medical care at Lone Tree Family Practice.  Dr. Linares is married with three beautiful girls. She enjoys hiking in the mountains, skiing, tennis and a good glass of red wine.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: Michelle graduated from the Physician Assistant Program at Marquette University in 2007 after completing her undergraduate degree in Biomedical Sciences. Upon graduation, she moved to Colorado and has gained valuable experience working as a Primary Care Provider in the Denver area and loves all that this beautiful state has to offer. She thoroughly enjoys the medical specialty of Family Practice and its concern for the total health of the individual as well as the family. She loves getting to know her patients and their family and watching them grow through the years.As a Midlevel Provider she sees patients for acute care, physicals, as well as chronic disease management. Within this area, Michelle has developed specific interests in health maintenance by helping patients form an interest in their own health through the use of preventative screenings and encouragement of a vigorous, healthy and well-balanced lifestyle and nutrition. Her professional interests include pediatrics, womens health, and sports medicine, and she is able to see all ages we see here at Lone Tree Family Practice.Outside of work you may see Michelle out running, on her bike, or an area hiking trail. She also enjoys participating in Triathlons and has a fond enjoyment of travel.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: Lynn received her Master of Science in Nursing\/Family Nurse Practitioner degree at the University of Colorado Health Sciences Center in 2007. Three years earlier, she completed her Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from the University of Iowa. She gained valuable experience as a Medical\/Surgical nurse in the hospital setting during graduate school and loved living in Colorado so much, she stayed to pursue her NP career.She worked for 6 years in an outpatient endocrinology clinic where she gained valuable experience and became an expert in managing a variety of diabetic and thyroid patients. She worked extensively on weight management and counseled patients on healthier lifestyles with diet and exercise. She has advanced experience using Armour and Cytomel in addition to Synthroid for thyroid hormone replacement.She is board certified by the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) and is excited to be back in family practice. In this setting, she still specializes in thyroid diseases and diabetes, but also manages a variety of medical conditions for all ages. She has experience in diagnosing and treating acute and chronic conditions across the lifespan, as well as performing physical exams. She likes to focus on preventive medicine and education to help patients live their best lives.In her free time, she loves traveling with her fiance and spending time with her dog. She also likes skiing, exercising, reading, and socializing with friends and family.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: Dr. Cedars practiced in Denver for thirty years prior to opening Lone Tree Family Practice with Dr. Linares in 2003. He graduated from University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in Dallas and completed two years of surgical residency prior to going into family medicine. He enjoys surgical procedures including vasectomies, skin lesion removals, biopsies and orthopedic procedures. Dr. Cedars has also been board certified in family medicine. He is a pas president of the Clear Creek Valley Medical Society. Currently he is a Delegate of the Colorado Medical Society and a member of the AMA and AAFP. He is on the Board of Directors of the Colorado Academy of Family Physicians and represents the CAFP on the multi-group committee on Patient Centered Medical Home. In addition to seeing patients, his duties include management of the office. He is married, has five grown children and seven grandchildren. His hobbies include flying, scuba diving and traveling with his family.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: A native of Colorado, Monica moved to northern Wisconsin where she earned her undergraduate degree from the University of Wisconsin education system in Eau Claire, WI.  In 2006, Monica moved to Iowa City to earn her Masters Degree in Physician Assistant Studies from the University of Iowa and has been practicing as a Certified Physician Assistant in Colorado since August 2008.Since beginning her practice, Monica dedicated her first 5 years of practice to serving the under and un-insured population of the Denver Metro area with Metro Community Provider Network (MCPN).  In early 2009, while still with MCPN, Monica partnered with Dr. Jose Castillo-Mancilla, MD of the University of Colorado to staff the MCPN HIV clinic and has since developed a deep interest and dedication for caring for those living with HIV and AIDS as well as addressing the primary prevention of HIV.  She then joined Lone Tree Family Practice in late 2013 to expand her practice and experience, be closer to home, and free up some of her time to spend with family and friends.Monicas professional skills and interests include the management and prevention of HIV\/AIDS (including HAART and PrEP prescription); and she is skilled and trained in performing basic office procedures including the placement of IUDs and general dermatologic procedures.  She has also been through specialized hormone evaluation and replacement training for both males and females.  Her professional interests and priorities include preventive and proactive health care, nutrition, diet and exercise counseling, and educating patients on how to best care for themselves to live a more healthy and well-balanced and active lifestyle.An avid runner, weekend yogi, suburban gardener, budding snowboarder and evening chef  she lives locally in Highlands Ranch with her husband, Bryan and small dog, Mocha.  She considers Colorado her true and forever home and in her spare time can be found enjoying the beauty of nature, reading a good book, sipping a cup of coffee or enjoying the occasional glass of wine or local craft microbrew beer.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio: Tammy has been a Certified Adult Nurse Practitioner since 1998.  For 15 years, she worked in Endocrinology developing her expertise in diabetes care, thyroid disease and management and hormone replacement therapy.  From the first elevated blood sugar to intensive insulin pump therapy, Tammy partners with her patients to achieve the best control they can.  Well versed in multiple thyroid preparations, including Armour Thryoid and T3 products, she works closely with the patients to find safe and optimal levels to help patients feel their best.   She believes health care is a partnership between the provider and the patient facilitated by information, education and empowerment.She received her Bachelors of Science in Nursing from the University of Texas and her Masters of Science in Nursing for Adult Primary Care from the University of Colorado Health Science Center.  Tammy has worked in health care since 1986 in the areas of critical care, geriatrics and general medicine.Tammy, a native Texan, is married and has raised her two sons here in Colorado.  She enjoys traveling, reading about traveling, and talking about her travels.  She loves to paint and read and has been known to enjoy a nice glass of wine on occasion.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio: Mary has provided health care services to women for the last 20 years first as a womens health nurse and now as a certified nurse midwife (CNM). She is passionate about helping women through all phases of their life and wants to ensure that her patients age gracefully. She became very interested in hormone replacement therapy (HRT) as a way for her to have additional tools to deliver excellent care to her patients.Through this pursuit, Mary is also skilled in assisting men with hormone issues that when addressed correctly can affect their physical and mental health as well as their longevity: Mary has consistently pursued higher education as a means to deliver better care to her patients. She is constantly striving to improve the care for her patients.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio: Barbara Slocum is a board certified Women's Health Nurse Practitioner and a full scope Certified Nurse Midwife. While growing up in a military family and living in many different locations, she considers Colorado home.She graduated from Air Academy High School in Colorado Springs and went on to attend Saint Mary's College in Notre Dame, Indiana, where she received a Bachelor of Science in Biology (with a minor in German). Barbara then completed the Accelerated Nursing Program at the Catholic University of America in Washington D.C. earning a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.Following graduation, she received a position at the prestigious Washington Hospital Center New Graduate Fellowship Program in high-risk labor and delivery. Upon completion of the fellowship program, she returned to Colorado.Barbara continued her work in high-risk OB care at various hospitals in Colorado. In 2012, she began work on her Masters of Science in Nursing at Georgetown University. This unique and difficult program provided an expanded focus on care for women and newborns that enabled her to sit for both the Women's Health Nurse Practitioner boards and the Certified Nurse Midwife board examinations. Barbara completed the clinical hours required for her Masters at Lone Tree OB\/GYN & Midwives and began working with the practice in 2014. She delivers at Skyridge Medical Center and Castle Rock Adventist Hospital.Additionally, Barbara VanDersarl Slocum is a published author! She was asked to write a chapter for the book, Pharmacology for Womens Health while in graduate school. Lone Tree OBGYN is thrilled to announce this book was recognized by the American Journal of Nursing as a Book of the Year and it received the top award in the Maternal-Child category. This is a notable accomplishment in nursing circles. Barbara is hopeful the information in the book will benefit more providers and make a difference for women around the world.Barbara and her husband John have three children. They enjoy spending time outdoors, running as well as playing and watching sports. Her ultimate goal of OB care is to provide compassionate, quality care that results in a healthy mom and a healthy baby.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio: Wayne C. Furr, MD of Lone Tree OB\/GYN & Midwives, is a board-certified obstetrician and gynecologist who's been practicing for over 30 years. He attended Loma Linda University School of Medicine and did his residency at White Memorial Medical Center in Los Angeles.The multicultural nature of his residency experience has proven beneficial over the years of his practice, and his learning of Spanish has assisted him in mission trips to clinics in South and Central America. Dr. Furr served in active reserve U.S. Air Force from 1980-1982, Edwards AFB, California, and was honorably discharged in 1982 as Major.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Board Certification  American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative MedicineBoard Certification  American Board of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation with a sub-specialty in Pain MedicineFellowship  Baylor University Medical Center, TXFellowship  St. Anthony Hospital, OKResidency  Carolinas Medical Center, NCInternship - Walter Reed Army Medical Center, DCMedical School - Medical College of Virginia, VADarryl D. Robinson, M.D. was born and raised in Richmond, Virginia. He obtained his undergraduate degree from Howard University in Washington, D.C. where he graduated Phi Beta Kappa, Magnum Cum Laude in 1991. He then went on to the Medical College of Virginia, Richmond, Virginia where he was awarded both the Alumni and Health Professional Scholarships, graduating in 1995.In 1995 Dr. Robinson was commissioned as a Captain into the United States Army and completed an Internship at Walter Reed Army Medical Center in 1996. From 1996 through 1998 he worked as a General Medical Officer at Winn Army Community Hospital, Fort Stewart, Georgia. He resigned his active duty commission in 1998 and continued in the individual ready reserves through 2004.Dr. Robinson completed a Residency in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation at Carolinas Medical Center, Charlotte, North Carolina in 2001. From 2001 through 2002 he completed a sub-specialty Fellowship in Pain Medicine via Baylor University  Saint Anthony North Ambulatory Surgery Center, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma.Dr. Robinson became a member of Oklahoma Sports Science and Orthopedics in 2002 and is Board Certified by the American Board of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation with a sub-specialty in Pain Medicine.After more than a decade of providing comprehensive, state of the art treatment for pain syndromes, Dr Robinson in 2012 was acknowledged by Castle Connolly as one of the regions top physicians. One thing that has become apparent is that pain programs that rely primarily on conventional pharmaceutical medications are limited. For this reason Dr. Robinson began to search for treatment alternatives that would expand his comprehensive approach and improve clinical outcomes. This approach focuses on optimizing the bodys natural functional and restorative capacity via the tenants of nutrition, hormone optimization, and wellness.In pursuit of the most heavily researched and vetted approaches, he became a Certified Fellow and Board Certified by the American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine. These concepts have served as his inspiration as medical director of Longevity Health, Beauty, and Wellness. In 2012 Dr. Robinson was also selected into the inaugural class of Pink Tie Guys by the Susan G. Komen affiliate in Central and Western Oklahoma to serve as an ambassador for womens health in the fight against breast cancer.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Grant Roberts, Physician Assistant, has been working with Dr. Robinson since 2003. Under the supervision of Dr. Robinson, Grant treats patients in the clinic and is available to see patients Monday-Friday 8:00 to 5:00. Grant graduated from the University of Oklahoma Physician Associate Program in 2001. He is a member of the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants (NCCPA). Grant is also a member of the Oklahoma Academy of Physicians Assistants (OAPA).

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Michelle Wray is a graduate of East Central University where she received her Bachelors of Science degree in Physics. She completed her masters of Health Science at the University of Oklahoma college of medicine and is a certified Physician Associate by the National Commission on certification of Physician Associates. Prior to receiving her Physician Associates degree, she worked in a laboratory performing DNA analysis for prostate cancer as well as fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) analysis to detect chromosomal abnormalities associated with bladder cancer. Her professional memberships includes the Oklahoma Academy of Physician Assistants as well as the American Academy of Physician Assistants. Her interests as a Physician Associate include; diet, exercise and overall health and wellness.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Amber Stachmus, PA-CMy belief is that keeping a positive attitude is the key to Longevity. I am a Board Certified and Oklahoma State licensed physician assistant who specializes in medical aesthetics with a focus on state-of-the-art laser procedures, fillers and injectables. I have a proven background in aesthetics, and a passion for minimally invasive techniques for clients wanting a non-surgical approach to self-improvement. In my free time I like to spend time with my kids, and animals.Masters of Health Science, University of Oklahoma, College of Medicine.Bachelors of Biologic Sciences, Oklahoma State University.Memberships include: The National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants (NCCPA); The Oklahoma Academy of Physicians Assistants (OAPA); American Academy of Physician Assistants (AAPA).

name: Los Alamitos Family Health and Wellness
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
bio: Dr. Ben Palombo is a native of Lafayette, LA in the heart of Cajun Country. He has a Bachelor of Science from Louisiana State University, and a Masters of Science as well as a Medical Degree from the American University of the Caribbean School of Medicine. After graduation, he obtained his post-graduate residency training in Family Medicine at LSU Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, LA, where he was also first introduced to Aesthetic Medicine. He relocated to Pineville, LA, where he established Premier Care Family Medicine as well as Faces Medical Spa and Wellness. One year into practice, he began to experience extreme fatigue, foggy thinking, decreased libido, and weight gain. His investigation into his own symptoms led him to discover the power and importance of proper hormone levels. He has continued to educate himself on this subject and now uses this knowledge to help his patients receive symptom relief. His journey has now led him a more effective treatment for hormone therapy: bio-identical hormone pellets.

name: Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Pineville
bio: Dr. Ben Palombo is a native of Lafayette, LA in the heart of Cajun Country. He has a Bachelor of Science from Louisiana State University, and a Masters of Science as well as a Medical Degree from the American University of the Caribbean School of Medicine. After graduation, he obtained his post-graduate residency training in Family Medicine at LSU Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, LA, where he was also first introduced to Aesthetic Medicine. He relocated to Pineville, LA, where he established Premier Care Family Medicine as well as Faces Medical Spa and Wellness. One year into practice, he began to experience extreme fatigue, foggy thinking, decreased libido, and weight gain. His investigation into his own symptoms led him to discover the power and importance of proper hormone levels. He has continued to educate himself on this subject and now uses this knowledge to help his patients receive symptom relief. His journey has now led him a more effective treatment for hormone therapy: bio-identical hormone pellets.

name: Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Pineville
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Pineville
Louisville Orthopaedic Clinic & Sports Rehabilitation Center PSC
Louisville Orthopaedic Clinic & Sports Rehabilitation Center PSC
Lourdes Uribe, MD PA
bio: Kareena A. Garza MPAS PA-CI attended the Univeristy of Texas Pan American Fall 2008- Spring 2011 where I obtained A Bachelor Degree in Biology with a minor in Chemistry and Psychology. I then persued my Masters in Physican Assistant Studies at The Univeristy of Texas Pan American from Fall 2011-Fall 2013. I first began my career as a physician assistant practicing in Pediatric Medicine at The Pediatric Care Center in  2014. I currently practice Women's Health at an Obstetrics and Gynecology office alongside Pediatric Medicine.

name: Lovitt Regenerative & Sexual Wellness
bio: Dr. Lovitt , a well-respected Denver Gynecologist went to medical school at Tulane School of Medicine, in New Orleans and did her residency at Alton Ochsner Medical Foundation, New Orleans, LA. She is Board Certified in OB\/GYN in Denver but decided to solely shift her focus on Hormone Replacement Therapy, Regenerative Medicine and Sexual Wellness since there are very few providers specializing in this much needed area of medicine.

name: Lovitt Regenerative & Sexual Wellness
bio: Sylvia Vigil is a native Coloradoan.   She earned a bachelor's degree in Biology and Microbiology from CSU in 1996.  She started Physician Assistant School at University of Colorado Health Sciences Center and completed the program May of 2000.  Her time in practice includes working in Family Medicine, Gynecology, Student Health, and Otolaryngology.  Sylvia has enjoyed managing dermatology, hormone health, complementary and alternative medicine, and aesthetics. Working at Lovitt Regenerative Medicine and Sexual Health has allowed her to work in all these capacities. Sylvia has been married to her husband Chris for over 15 years and they have 3 sons. Sylvia enjoys camping, knitting\/crocheting, reading, watching the Broncos, and attending her boys' extracurricular activities.

name: LowTE Florida
bio: Nurse Practitioner Carolyn Zaumeyer has been specializing in womens health (gynecology) for more than 20 years. She is the author of two books and more than 27 publications, has served on the Advisory Board of the Duke\/Johnson & Johnson Nurse Leadership Program and is an established public speaker, having presented nationally and internationally at more than 100 conferences.After establishing the first independent nurse practitioner practice in Florida in 1994, Carolyn has become a well-known expert and resource for nurse practitioners embarking on business ownership, womens health, and Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement TherapyAfter the Womens Health Initiative Trial in 2002 revealed that synthetic hormones could increase womens risk of breast cancer, heart attack, stroke, blood clots and Alzheimers disease, Carolyn decided to devote her studies to Bio-Identical Hormones. She wanted to learn how to prescribe them safely and effectively. Carolyn has traveled throughout the United States and has studied under the most prominent experts in Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy (BHRT)  Dr. Sangeeta Pati in Orlando, Dr. Neil Rouzier in Salt Lake City, Dr. Daved Rosensweet in Naples, Florida and Dr. Gary Donovitz in Dallas. She is knowledgeable of all the delivery methods of hormone replacement and is especially excited and satisfied with the BioTE pelleting system.Carolyn was the first BioTE Medical Certified Practitioner in Florida and was recently invited to become Faculty for BioTE Medical  providing BHRT training on the national level to physicians and Nurse Practitioners.As a proud member of the Forever Health Practitioner Network, whose national spokesperson is Suzanne Somers; Carolyn has worked with Suzanne on several projects. Carolyn and Suzanne have a great rapport and are like-minded in their beliefs of healthy aging and BHRT.Carolyn has dedicated her practice to BHRT to men and women, but also provides office gynecology and cosmetic injections at her Fort Lauderdale office.EDUCATIONBSN, MSN & ARNP Florida International UniversityStudied under 4 Internationally Known BHRT specialistsFirst Certified BioTE Provider in FloridaAWARDSMedical Advisory Board BioTE Medical, DallasBioTELegacy Provider, DallasAdvisory Board Duke-Johnson & Johnson Nurse Leadership ProgramOutstanding Alumni  Florida International University, Miami

name: Lubbock Plastic Surgery Institute
bio: Heidi Jeffreys has been a member of Physician Network Services since she graduated from the Texas Tech Physician Assistant Program in 2005.She worked as a hospitalist at University Medical Center in Lubbock providing inpatient care to internal medicine patients on med\/surge and ICU floors until 2008. During this time she was a preceptor for Texas Tech physician assistant students during their clinical rotations. In September of 2008, she moved to Fresh Outlook. Heidi has always had a passion for wellness and healthy living in an aging population. In keeping with this, she continues to see elderly patients part-time who require evaluation in a nursing home setting. Heidi has added the specialty of bio-identical hormone replacement therapy using pellets to her services for all of her patients as her passion for wellness continues to grow.Heidi is happily married to her husband, Andrew. They met in Alaska while doing their undergraduate work. In Alaska, she enjoyed many outdoor activities such as hiking, salmon fishing, skiing and snowmobiling. She continues to enjoy outdoor activities as well as yoga and Pilates. She has two young children, Ian is five and Alexia is two.

name: Luis A. Cruz, MD
address: Ponce De Leon 735 Suite 505 Torre Auxilio Mutuo Hato Rey

name: LuminCare
bio: Sandy Stetz is a Physician Assistant with a background in Emergency Medicine. She graduated from the Essex, Maryland, Physician Assistant program and went on to earn a Bachelor of Arts in Communication Arts with a Biology minor. She spent 11 years at Peninsula Regional Medical Center, in Salisbury, Maryland, working in the Emergency Department of this regional Trauma center. Later, she earned a Master's in Post Secondary Education from Salisbury University and taught at the University of Maryland, Physician Assistant Program, Princess Anne, Maryland, where she was the Academic Coordinator, Student Advisor and faculty. She has worked in various practice settings including Urgent Care, College Health, Urology, Occupational and Family Medicine. She has a strong interest in nutrition and focuses on healthful lifestyles as a way to prevent serious health problems. She has been trained in pelleting procedures for Bioidentical hormone replacement. Additionally, she is certified in Botox and dermal fillers, for facial contouring. Her multi-cultural perspective is enhanced by extensive travel to developing nations on short-term medical missions and disaster relief trips.

name: Luttrell Surgical and Healthy Aging
bio: Dr. Luttrell was born in El Dorado, Arkansas. After graduating from the University of Arkansas at Little Rock he attended medical school at St. George's University in Bay Shore, New York and Kent & Canterbury Hospital in Canterbury, Kent England. Dr. Luttrell completed his Internal Medicine and General Surgery residencies at the James H. Quillen College of Medicine in Johnson City, Tennessee. Since entering practice in 1993, Dr. Luttrell has performed thousands of surgical procedures including nearly 1,000 Gastric Bypasses for obesity.Dr. Luttrell is board certified by the American Board of Surgery and by the American Board of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine. He is also a member of the American Medical Association, the American Society for Bariatric and Metabolic Surgery, the Southern Medical Association, the Pulaski County Medical Society, the Arkansas Medical Society and the American College of Surgeons. He has won the Internal Medicine Award of Excellence, membership in Alpha Omega Alpha Honorary Society, and a Dean's Award for Excellence in Teaching.

name: M.D.'s Weight and Wellness Center, PA
M.D.'s Weight and Wellness Center, PA
MacArthur Center for Hormone Balance & Wellness
bio: Dr. John Zavaleta was born and raised in Brownsville, Texas. He graduated from the University of Texas in Austin with honors in Pharmacy. He practiced as a pharmacist for three years before deciding to go to medical school. He then graduated from the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in 1981, followed by his residency at Baylor Medical Center in Dallas where he was Chief Resident specializing in Obstetrics and Gynecology. Womens health has been his passion since he began his practice in 1985. He believes it is important that his patients have the quality of life they deserve. He is a Diplomat of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, and the American Urogynecologic Society, and a member of the Society of Urodynamics, Female Pelvic Medicine, and Urogenital Reconstruction. He keeps current with the most advanced procedures in womens healthcare. Dr. Zavaleta was recently chosen to be one of a handful of investigators across the country to do research for a major national company that produces biologic material for surgical procedures.  He has been a board-certified gynecologist for over 25 years and has accrued over 700 hours of continuing medical education in the area of incontinence, bladder dysfunction, and pelvic floor anatomy and rehabilitation.  Dr. Zavaleta believes his patients should feel comfortable in his office, and should feel free to express their concerns. It is his personal commitment to ensure his patients quality of life through superior care and the most current procedures and resources available today.

name: MacArthur Center for Hormone Balance & Wellness
Maidenhair Hormone Clinic for Women
bio: Dr. Brenden Witte is a Naturopathic Medical Doctor focusing in mens health.  He specializes in bioidentical testosterone replacement therapy and sexual\/reproductive health.  By combining effective scientific medical techniques and naturopathic, common sense approaches to lifestyle, Dr. Witte has become a BioTE certified physician in pellet therapy.  He provides BioTEs method which supports optimal health and vitality, addressing and treating both the symptoms and the root cause of low energy, weight gain, poor mental acuity and erectile dysfunction in men.

name: Maintain Youth Age
bio: Kyle Dailey O'Hara, RN is the founder and co-owner of Maintain Youth Medical Aesthetics and has over over twenty years nursing experience in the clinical practice of age restorative medical and aesthetic treatments.Kyle began her training as a cosmetic and reconstructive plastic surgery nurse in 1990 with Dr. David Apfelberg, founder of the the prestigious Atherton Plastic Surgery Center. Kyle pioneered nurse applications in dermatology laser treatments, dermal fillers, sclerotherapy and laser hair removal through her work at the Atherton Plastic Surgery Center.Kyle went on to become an international clinical trainer of physicians in dermatology laser applications, dermal fillers, chemical peel and neuro-modulator treatment applications.In additional to her clinical nursing skills in plastic surgery and dermatology, Kyle is also a skilled practitioner in holistic age management and is certified in Physician Level Intravenous Nutritional Therapy. Kyle has been a Registered Nurse for 35 years and is a graduate of West Virginia Northern School of Nursing

name: Maintain Youth Age
bio: Harlan L. South, MD, FACP, an experienced physician and former Lieutenant Colonel in the US Army, is a native of Richmond Virginia. After graduating Magna Cum Laude in Biochemistry and Chemistry from NC State in 1990 and obtaining his medical degree from the Medical College of Virginia in 1996, he completed his internship and residency at MCV. He was board certified by the American Board of Internal Medicinein 2002 and named as a Fellow of the American College of Physicians in 2005. His military service included a yearlong tour in Ramadi, Iraq as a Battalion Surgeon. While continuing to fulfill his military obligations, Dr. South was a practicing internist in Georgia for 10 years prior to joining our practice in May 2009. Dr. South is now certified to perform Class 2 and 3 flight physicals. He and his wife, Kadie Tabassian, a practicing dentist in Buckhead, have one daughter. Dr. South enjoys reading, exercising, and traveling.

name: Manuel J Rodriguez Iglesias MD
address: 63 Mendez Vigo E Centro Plaza, Of. 3A

name: Maria Cole Family Practice
bio: Maria is a Family Nurse Practitioner, Board Certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners, and licensed by the State of Texas to provide family centered health care to patients of all ages. Her scope of practice encompasses health promotion and health maintenance education, diagnosis and management of common health care problems, sports physical examinations, and routine well-women care.Marias academic background includes a Bachelor of Science in Nursing and Master of Science from the Family Nurse Practitioner program at Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center School of Nursing. During her undergraduate studies she worked as a registered nurse where she gained a wide variety of experience in infertility, family care and womens health care. Maria is a native from Big Spring, Texas.Maria strives to provide the best health care possible. She believes in acquiring a comprehensive evaluation of every patient by taking time to listen and understand their particular needs. Her true desire is to cultivate a professional environment where each patient feels comfortable, receives focused attention and is given competent care.

name: Maria Cole Family Practice
bio: Kelly is a Family Nurse Practitioner and is Board Certified from the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners and licensed by the Texas Board of Nursing to provide family centered health care to patients of all ages.  Kelly has a Masters Degree in Nursing from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center. She is also licensed as a surgical first assist.Kelly was born and raised in Odessa. She attended schools in Odessa.  After completing a four year scholarship in softball\/volleyball, Kelly returned to Odessa to pursue a nursing degree. Kelly found her calling in nursing and is happy to be able to give back to the West Texas area she loves.  In the past 18 years, Kelly has had the benefit of working for and with some of the best medical professionals West Texas has to offer. She has experience in pediatrics, cardiology, orthopedics as well as emergency medicine. Kelly enjoys being able to treat and care for the entire family.

name: Marian Zinnante MD
bio: Kimberly is a nationally certified Adult Nurse Practitioner. She is an accomplished provider with experience in Endocrinology, Bariatrics, Gastroenterology, and Preventative Medicine. She is a former certified personal trainer, marathoner, and brown belt in Tae Kwon Do.Kimberly has formal training in psychology and alternative medicine\/acupressure, and received her masters degree from the University of San Diego. She is committed to the philosophies of preventative medicine and to treating the patient as a whole.When you look beyond symptoms and disease and take time to truly understand the history and circumstances in which they were born, you are able to treat the root of the problem, minimize (if not eliminate) symptoms, and enable the patient to head off a multitude of potential complications.

name: Marie Hatfield, APRN, AGNP-BC
bio: Specializing in Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy, Low Testosterone Treatment and Medical Weight Loss. There are many different factors that can disrupt optimal hormone balance. It can be a part of the aging process, increased daily stress, peri-menopause, menopause, and lack of sleep to name a few. The resulting imbalance can cause a variety of different symptoms and leave you longing for your youthful vigor and vitality. She can help you get back to living a happy, healthy life and feeling good about yourself and who you are!  She has a passion for helping individuals achieve their best self and loves to encourage and support others on this life-changing journey. Maria has lived in Arkansas since she was 19 years old.  She attended the University of Arkansas in Fayetteville to obtain her bachelors degree in nursing and went on to the University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences in Little Rock to obtain her Advanced Nurse Practitioner degree. She has experience and is a certified advanced practice nurse in bio-identical hormone replacement therapy and medical supervised weight loss.  She has past nursing experience in the operating room, emergency room, cardiac cath lab as well as critical care. Marie is very active and her hobbies include kayaking, hiking, working-out and playing with her two precious dogs.

name: Mario A. Echavarria, M.D., Family Medicine
Marisol Health
bio: Dede Chism is the co-founder and Executive Director of Bella Natural Womens Care.  Her passion for women and their dignity led her to a career in nursing.  She earned her Masters Degree in Nursing with a specialty as a Perinatal Nurse Practitioner from Regis University in Denver, Colorado.  Dede has worked as a Nurse Practitioner specializing in high risk pregnancies for over 18 years with Obstetrix Medical Group and Swedish Medical Center prior to the conception of Bella. Dede participated in extensive continued medical education offered through the Pope Paul VI Institute.Dedes career in Nursing has taken her from critical care obstetrics and transporting pregnant women in helicopters with AirLife to authoring The High-Risk Pregnancy Sourcebook in 1997 through Lowell Publishing House, to expert medical consulting and to the high Andes of Peru coordinating medical missions.   An active member of the Christian Life Movement, Dede served on their council from 2009-2012 and participated as a US delegate and presenter for the Christian Life Movement at the International Plenary Assembly in Guayaquil, Equador in 2009 and has been asked to return as a US delegate for  the next Plenary Assembly Arequipa, Peru in 2015.Dede has a 30 year history in youth ministry and has been able to combine her nursing and youth ministry skills at World Youth Days in Denver, Paris and Toronto as well as serving for over a decade at Steubenville Youth Conferences. Dede was a contributing author on a book on Prayer published through LifeTeen.  Dede and her husband Ken have been married for 36 years and are blessed with 3 grown children, their spouses and 9 grandchildren.  Dede and Ken love wine and chocolate!  They love to travel, spend time in the outdoors hiking, biking, snowshoeing, fishing, reading and enjoying Gods majestic beauty from mountains to seas.

name: Marisol Health
bio: Abby is the co-founder and Associate Director of Bella Natural Womens Care.  She graduated from the University of Colorado with her Masters in Science and is a Board Certified Womens Health Nurse Practitioner. After receiving her undergraduate degree from Regis University, Abby worked as a Labor and Delivery nurse for seven years.  Abby has completed the Nurse Practitioner Medical Consultant training through the Pope Paul IV Institute and is a Creighton Model Practitioner Intern and is committed to excellent obstetric and gynecologic care that promotes the dignity of Women.Abbys passion for preserving the dignity of women started long before her career in medicine.  She has been involved in youth and young adult ministry since high school.  Abby served for a year as a missionary with the National Evangelization Teams (NET Ministries) and has spoken at conferences throughout the country to young women affirming their beauty and dignity.  As a teenager, Abby had the opportunity to see the birth of a baby where she felt as if angels were dancing around the room.   She was drawn to the way the medical team worked in cooperation with the woman and family.  One of these team members was her mom, Dede.  She knew that one day she would be a part of that team.Abby and her husband Justin are missionaries at heart and have served with the Christian Life Movements medical missions in Ayaviri, Peru.  Not only does her work and ministry life focus on womens issues, but Abby and her husband have three young daughters Olivia, Madelynn and Mary Belle.  Abby is blessed among women!  Abby enjoys camping, swimming, snowboarding and being surrounded by the ones she loves.

name: Marisol Health
bio: Leigh Bauer is a board certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist. She attended undergrad at the University of St. Thomas in St. Paul, Minnesota and then went on to medical school at Des Moines University. Dr. Bauer was blessed with the opportunity to do her obstetrics and gynecology rotation with Dr. Hilgers in Omaha, NE which helped her decide that she wanted to specialize as an OB\/GYN. Dr. Bauer embraced helping women figure out their menstrual cycles and helping them as they worked through infertility. After a four-year residency in Buffalo, New York, Dr. Bauer accepted a position in a hospital based OB\/GYN practice in Northern Minnesota for three years prior to coming to Colorado.Dr. Bauer was drawn to be a prolife physician as a teenager when her primary care doctor thought it was her obligation to council her about safe sex and being on birth control. It was frustrating for her and her mother when they assured the doctor she was committed to abstinence until marriage and the doctor told them all teenagers are sexually active. Dr. Bauer then met a wonderful family physician who encouraged abstinence until marriage and believed in them and their commitment to wait for marriage. It was so refreshing to have such a great doctor. This physician then invited her shadow her at a prolife clinic and Dr. Bauer witnessed the compassionate care to women from all walks of life that she herself desired as a physician.Dr. Bauer and her husband, Jordan, are originally from Minnesota. They have three children: Seamus, Virginia and Danika. They are so excited to be living in Colorado and are having so much fun exploring the city of Denver and getting out into the mountains for hiking and exploring. Dr. Bauer is an avid runner and loves to spend as much time as she can in the beautiful Colorado sunshine!

name: Marisol Health
bio: Dr. Hodack is the family medicine physician at Bella Natural Womens Care and Family Wellness. Sarah received her undergraduate degree from Colorado State University (Go Rams!) and she attended medical school at Creighton University. Dr. Hodack worked at a family medicine clinic in Greeley, Colorado for 5 years before joining the Bella team in 2016. She pursued medicine because she finds the human body fascinating and she loves helping others through their medical issues so that they can live life to the full. Dr. Hodack views her job as a physician as a mission to serve every patient with dignity as a beloved child of God.  She is certified in family medicine and loves the wide variety of patients she is able to see all across the lifespan. She especially enjoys caring for obstetric and pediatric patients.  Dr. Hodack has been married to her husband, Troy, for five years. They have three children: Lucy, Finn and Clare. She is originally from Buena Vista, Colorado and loves reading, running, swimming and traveling.

name: Marisol Health
bio: Sharon is a Colorado native and was raised in Loveland CO with her three sisters. She graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in nursing in 1982 from the University of Northern Colorado. Initially, Sharon worked as a Labor and Delivery Nurse until entering her graduate program through Regis University, she graduated in 1992 as a Perinatal Nurse Practitioner. For 25 years, she worked with high risk obstetrical patients in both the inpatient and outpatient setting. Sharon enjoyed the joys and challenges in managing complicated pregnancies to provide the best outcome possible for every pregnancy. Sharon began working for Bella in Oct 2016. She especially enjoys educating pregnant women in promoting maintenance of healthy lifestyle, not only during pregnancy, but throughout a womans lifespan. Sharon and her husband John have been married for 30 years and have three grown children. They enjoy spending time with their children and large extended families, as well as spending time in the great Colorado outdoors hiking, sailing, snow shoeing and traveling to new places. Sharon also enjoys gardening, cooking and reading.

name: Marissa Magsino MD
bio: Marissa Magsino, M.D. dedicates her Orlando-based bioidentical hormones practice to helping her patients overcome health obstacles brought on by the bodys aging process. Dr. Magsino helps women and men find relief from symptoms of hormonal imbalance such as menopause, weight gain, adrenal fatigue, low libido, hot flashes, night sweats, mood swings, and depression, using a structured regimen consisting of bioidentical hormone therapy and customized nutrition and fitness programs.Dr. Magsino practiced internal medicine for 15 years before making the decision to transition into integrative and regenerative medicine. Her decision was largely influenced by her desire to help her patients age gracefully, with preventive techniques and proactive care. As a part of BioTE Medical, Dr. Magsino is able to work closely with each patient to customize a treatment plan that best suits them, enabling her to treat the individual and not just the symptoms.Marissa Magsino, M.D. received her undergraduate from the University of Philippines and completed her doctorate at the University of the East in 1986. Dr. Marissa Magsino fulfilled her Residency in Internal Medicine and Pediatrics at the University of Medicine and Dentistry, Newark, New Jersey in 1997. Dr. Magsino is Board Certified in Internal Medicine and served as President of the Philippine American Physicians of Central Florida from 2007 to 2009. Dr. Magsino is an active member of the Fellowship in Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine.

name: Mark McTammany OB\/GYN
bio: Mark S. McTammany, M.D., F.A.C.O.G., received his medical degree from George Washington University in Washington D.C.  He completed his residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the Western Pennsylvania Hospital in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, receiving Resident of the Year honors as Chief Resident.  He has practiced Obstetrics and Gynecology in the Melbourne area since 1997 and was honored as Central Floridas Best OB\/GYN by Channel 9 News in 2000.Dr. McTammany is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: Mark Quiring MD
bio: Dr. Mark Quiring is a native Texan and has lived in Mt. Pleasant for the past 18 years. He is a Board Certified Family Medicine Physician that practices primary care. Hes had a private practice in Mt. Pleasant since 1998. From Dallas originally, he attended the University of Monterrey in Monterrey, Mexico where he received his medical degree. Finishing his Family Practice Residency training and as a Chief Resident in Pennsylvania returning to Texas to begin his practice.   In addition to his family practice, Dr. Quiring also added on Botox and fillers some time ago. He recently became a BioTe Certified Practitioner and is truly looking forward to helping his patients feel better and having an overall better sense of well being. He is truly passionate about his patients and when you visit his office you will be treated as you are the only patient. No rushing  he wants to get to the root of the problem and will do everything he can to make you feel your best!  In Dr. Quirings free time he enjoys playing golf, snowboarding in the winter, water sports including scuba diving and on most weekends he finds time to play drums with his own rock and roll band.

name: Mark Reecer MD
bio: Dr. Mark Reecer is board certified in Physical Medicine & Rehabilitation and Pain Management. He has over 20 years of work comp experience, and he routinely provides Independent Medical Examinations (IMEs) for the Indiana Workers Compensation Board. Dr. Reecer has lectured extensively and has authored multiple publications that promote his specialty and the use of treatment modalities to eliminate pain, improve function and avoid surgery.

name: Mark Scroggins MD
bio: Dr. Scroggins has worked in this area since 1981  thats over 30 years in the Mid-Cities! Reliability, dependability, and commitment are truly what he stands for. He is certified by the Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a fellow of the American College of OB-GYN.Dr. Scroggins was salutatorian of his high school class in Dallas, Texas. He then graduated with high honors from the University of Texas at Arlington. Afterwards, he completed medical school at the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston. Dr. Scroggins spent four years specializing in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Texas affiliated hospital in the medical center in Houston, Texas. This includes Hermann Hospital and MD Anderson Cancer Center.Being a solo practitioner allows Dr. Scroggins to have more hands-on care. No big group atmosphere where patients are rotated among many doctors. He delivers over 90% of his obstetrical patients himself-no midwives, nurse practitioners, and other health care providers that patients are rotated through.Dr. Scroggins is experienced but stays current on the newest technology as well, from 3D\/4D sonography to use of the Da Vinci Robotic System.In addition to obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. Scroggins has expanded his practice in 2014 to include bioidentical hormones in the form of Biote. This has been a life transforming treatment for many patients. In 2015, the practice was expanded to the prescribing of suboxone to help those with opiate dependence. Dr. Scroggins began this after suboxone made a major improvement in the life of a close family member.He allows natural OB deliveries, however specializes in deliveries with minimal pain and discomfort.Dr. Scroggins is a Dallas Cowboys and Mavs fan, as well as a fan of The Voice. He studies American political history and collects political Americana, especially political buttons that have been produced since 1896.Dr. Scroggins married his college sweetheart and have two children, a son and a daughter, as well as one grandchild. He and his daughter have attended I Love Lucy conventions, and enjoyed Elvis conventions as well. He and his son received advanced scuba certifications together and have traveled to the remote South Sea Islands to live on a dive boat for a week. His daughter has earned her doctorate at a local university. His son-in-law, continuing the medical tradition, has completed his fellowship in Interventional Cardiology and now is practicing locally.His son, also continuing the medical tradition, is studying pre-Veterinary Medicine in college.The whole Scroggins family is pet lovers. They recently acquired their 4th and 5th Cocker Spaniels since Dr. Scroggins started in medical practice. His newest puppies are a brother and sister pair of parti colored cocker spaniels named Bella and Winston. Winston was named after Dr. Scroggins hero, Winston Churchill. When all the family is home for the holidays, there are twelve pets in the home for five people, which includes three dogs, four cats, and five birds.

name: Marshall Urology & Continence Center
bio: Dr. Carter is board certified in adult and pediatric urology and brings a wealth of experience to the practice of urology. He has special interest and expertise in the treatment of prostate disorders, urologic cancers, stone disease, female incontinence, and male erectile dysfunction. Dr. Carter completed his urologic residency at the University of Southern California in Los Angeles in 1988, and has been in clinical practice since then. Marshall Urology was founded by Dr. Carter in 1997 as Marshall Urology Associates when he became the first full time urologist to live and practice in Marshall County. In 2006, our name was changed to Marshall Urology & Continence Center, PC, a name which reaffirms Dr. Carters commitment to excellent, patient-centered care in the practice of general urology, while also emphasizing his special interest in the evaluation and management of urinary incontinence issues in both adult and pediatric patients.Dr. Carter is on staff at both Marshall Medical Center North and Marshall Medical Center South. www.mmcenters.comDr. Carter and his family reside in Marshall County and are active in the community.

name: Masterpiece Centre of Aesthetics and Gynecology, LLC
MastersMD
bio: As a leader in the emerging field of Metabolic Medicine, Dr. Leslie Masters brings to the table an unmatched resume in education, training and experience in the areas of health, wellness and well-being.  Dr. Masters earned her Medical Degree from the University of Minnesota in 1994.  Currently, she is an advanced fellow of the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine and its earning her Masters Degree in Metabolic and Nutritional Medicine from the University of Southern Florida.Despite board certification in the areas of Internal Medicine and Medical Oncology, Masters true calling has become one of helping patients to live a life as happy, healthy, whole people.  In 2005 Dr. Masters left traditional medicine and opened MastersMD, a center for Metabolic and Cosmetic Medicine where health, wellness and well-being has become her focus.  Dr. Masters has been featured as a medical and wellness expert in numerous television, newspaper and radio news stories and interviews across the county, and has published three books in the areas of spiritual, mental and physical wellness.

name: Matlock Centre
bio: My name is Dr. Raymond Westbrook. I am a Medical Director Specializing in BHRT with years of clinical Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy experience, practicing in Arlington, TX .

name: Matthew St. Laurent MD
bio: Dr. Matthew St. Laurent is a proud native of Houston, Texas. He graduated Magna Cum Laude from the honors program at Texas A&M University with a degree in Biochemistry. Afterwards, he received his medical degree at Texas A&M University College of Medicine where he was recognized for surgical honors and graduated in the top of his class. Dr. St. Laurent subsequently completed his surgical training at the University of Texas Health Service Center in San Antonio, Texas. In addition to being named Bariatric Medical Director at Cy-Fair Medical Center, Dr. St. Laurent holds the position of Bariatric Medical Director at Journey Lite of Houston. He looks forward to working with hormone patients to complete the journey to a healthy life.

name: MaxHealth Family Medicine
bio: Bio Coming Soon!

name: May BioMedical
bio: Kevin G. May, MD, is a board-certified physician specializing in internal medicine at his practice, May Medical, located in Tyler, Texas. He provides a wide range of state-of-the-art services, including bioidentical hormone therapy, diabetes management, and heart disease prevention. Dr. May also offers a variety of innovative treatments for chronic conditions, like thyroid disorders, lipid disorders, and COPD.Dr. May is a diplomate of the American Board of Internal Medicine. He has been the recipient of several esteemed doctor awards, including On-Time Doctor award, Compassionate Doctor Recognition award, and the Patients Choice award.Before opening his current practice in Tyler, Dr. May proudly served the Department of Veterans Affairs from 2008 until 2014. While at the VA, Dr. May held various positions, including section chief of the Tyler VA Medical Clinic, chief of compensation and pension at the Dallas VA Medical Center, and finally as the chief medical officer of the two largest outpatient clinics at the South Texas Veterans Health Care System in San Antonio.Graduating from Abilene Christian University, Dr. May earned his medical degree from the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School. He finished his residency in internal medicine at the university hospitals within the University of Texas system in San Antonio. A native of Dallas, Dr. May is happy to return to the Rose Capital of America, a city that has always captivated his heart.Dr. May is committed to developing the patient-physician relationship after seeing the many changes taking place in the health care system. His belief that his true employers are his patients ensures his full attention and loyalty are dedicated to those he serves. He feels patients deserve better than a quick, five-minute visit and remains dedicated to providing the highest quality health care for every one of his patients.

name: McKinney Family Medicine
bio: Brian Charles Procter MD was born and raised in the Metroplex. Following graduation from Trinity High School in Euless, he attended The United States Naval Academy in Annapolis, Maryland. He earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Molecular Biology at The University of Texas at Austin. After a brief career in Molecular Biology in Houston, he attended Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center School of Medicine in Lubbock, Texas. He graduated with his Doctorate in Medicine in 1997. Dr. Procter completed his residency in Family Medicine at Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center in 2000. Following residency, Dr. Procter established Procter Family Healthcare in McKinney, Texas in 2000. In 2006, he moved to his present facility, McKinney Family Medicine. His medical interests include preventative medicine, chronic condition management, minor surgery, and psychiatry. In 2005, he established Nuvage Laser Medspa, and has become one of Collin Countys leading Botox and Juvederm providers. Over the past 7 years, he modernized McKinney Family Medicine using advanced healthcare technology systems in order to optimize the patient experience and deliver exceptional customer service. He is a leading consultant in healthcare information technology, practice management, and medical database development. He is a Diplomat of AAFP, and member of AMA, PPN, and Genesis Physicians Group. Dr. Procter lives in McKinney, Texas and has two children, Kaitlyn and Keira. In his spare time, he enjoys tennis, hunting, fishing, and travelling with his family.

name: McKinney Family Medicine
bio: Vanessa was born and raised in the DFW metro-plex and lives in McKinney with her husband and daughter. She received her Bachelor of Science in Biomedical Science from Texas A&M University in College Station in 2006. Vanessa graduated with honors in her Masters in Physician Assistant Studies at UNT Health Science in Fort Worth in May 2010. Family Medicine and Pediatrics have always been her passion because she enjoys building relationships with each and every member of the family. She spent a year in clinical rotations where she experienced all aspects of medicine including surgery, OB\/GYN, pediatrics, and an extended clerkship in family medicine. She also has experience in urgent care where she managed patients with minor surgical complaints and minor emergencies.In her spare time, she enjoys being with her family and friends, especially if it involves the outdoors. She likes to camp, go to the lake, ride ATV's and have backyard barbecues. She also has two dogs (a chocolate lab and a basset hound) who are considered part of the family and travel everywhere with them.

name: McKinney Family Medicine
bio: Erica R. Rios was born in Dallas, Texas and currently resides in Lewisville, Texas.  She received her Bachelors of Science with a Minor in Chemistry from Texas Womans University in December of 2004. She graduated with a Master of Physician Assistant Studies from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston December of 2008.  Family Medicine is her primary interest at heart because she enjoys focusing on health promotion as well as seeing a variety of all ages. Erica is also fluent in Spanish and is able to provide Spanish speaking services to those patients who desire it.  She particularly enjoys going to church and working out at her local Crossfit gym. During her spare time, Erica enjoys spending time with her family, friends, and husband Jake. Erica is currently a Physician Assistant at McKinney Family Medicine in McKinney, Texas.

name: McKinney Family Medicine
bio: Cortney grew up in McKinney, graduated from McKinney High School and currently resides in McKinney with her husband of 12 years with her 2 boys, Braxton and Lawson. She completed her undergraduate degree from Texas A&M University and Masters from University of North Texas Health Science Center. She has been in medicine for 16 years with a background in Cardiology, Pediatrics, Hospitalist Medicine and Holistic Health, and has been a practicing Physician Assistant for six years. She loves medicine, and getting to know her patients, and enjoys treating them like family. She is passionate about over all well-being and treating each patient individually. Aside from work, she loves spending time with her wonderful husband and 2 boys, as well as being outside, traveling and working out. She hopes she can provide the utmost care for you and your family and wishes to gain a relationship with each one of you. She believes every patient (and person) has a story, and we can all learn and benefit from listening and helping each other.

name: McLean Cares, Inc.
bio: Dr. McLean graduated from the Medical College of Georgia in August 1986. He has more than 30 years of practice in the medical field, with 25 of these years being in primary practice. He did his internship and residency in Family Medicine at the Medical Center of Macon, Georgia.He is a proud veteran of the Vietnam Era, having served 3 years in the U.S. Army.He is married to his wife of 32 years, Dr. L. T. McLean. They currently live in Thomasville, Georgia.Dr. McLean practices primary care medicine with special emphasis on bariatric care (weight management), personal injury, and hormone replacement therapy, while still continuing to have a passion for the nuts and bolts of his specialty, ie, hypertensive Cane, diabetic care, adolescent and geriatric medical care as well as respiratory care.He is the medical director of McLean Cares, Inc., with multiple locations. He has a passion for total patient care and insists he and his staff treat each patient as an extension of their family, with love, respect, privacy, and concern.Dr. McLean is a member of multiple organizations to include:-American Academy of Family Practice-Georgia Academy of Family Practice-SW Georgia Medical Association-American Board of Barialtic Medicine-American Society of Bariatric Physicians-National Medical Association-Griffin-Jordan Medical Society

name: MD Beauty Labs
bio: Daniela Dadurian, M.D., has been practicing Internal Medicine for over a decade. She specializes in Anti-Aging medicine, laser treatment and Cosmetic Medicine and has traveled the world researching the safest and latest technologies on the market. Dr. Dadurian received her medical degree from the University of Miami School of Medicine and is Board Certified in Anti-Aging Medicine*. Her expertise in anti-aging techniques and passion for excellence are reflected in the extraordinary and personal care she gives each patient. MD Beauty Labs at The Whitney in West Palm Beach was designed by Dr. Dadurian to provide Anti-Aging and Cosmetic services. This state of the art facility offers Medical, Spa and Body Treatments in a luxurious contemporary loft environment. With Dr. Dadurian's team of Nurses, Medical Estheticians, Massage Therapists, Permanent Makeup Specialist and Medical Spa Concierge, MD Beauty Labs is dedicated to providing a revitalizing experience.

name: MD Cosmedx Laser and Lipo Center
MD Cosmedx Laser and Lipo Center
bio: Sherri Newman, APRNSherri Newman, is a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner who has been practicing in Bowling Green, KY since 2010.  After graduating from WKU in 1994 with her BSN, she worked in the CCU setting for 4 years.  In 1998 she transitioned to the area of Health and Wellness.  Sherri saw the need for practitioners in Preventive and Anti-Aging care and decided to return to school to pursue a degree as a FNP.  Mrs. Newman began her career practicing part-time in a thriving weight loss clinic alongside Dr. Richard Welch.  After practicing for 2 years she realized that there is more to weight loss than just diet and exercise.  Experiencing hormone related changes herself she began researching hormone replacement therapy and the role hormones play in not only weight loss but also ones well-being.  Sherri knew this was the career path she wanted to continue after experiencing such positive results with her own hormone replacement therapy.

name: Meagan Moore Professional Medical Corporation
bio: Dr Meagan Moore attended the University of California at Santa Barbara and went on to earn her medical degree at Brown University. She completed her residency at the University of California, Irvine. Dr Moore is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology.Dr. Moore has a well balanced practice in both obstetrics and gynecology. She specializes in minimally invasive surgeries such as endometrial ablations and hysterectomies. Dr Moore has been trained in Da Vinci robotic surgery and has performed over 100 minimally invasive hysterectomies.Dr. Moore is a native Californian and now resides in Newport Beach with her family. She has been in the same private practice for 13 years and has developed long term relationships with her patients. She enjoys the balance of managing a busy practice while raising her three children.

name: Med Care
bio: I am a state board certified family nurse practitioner dedicated to providing you with premium health care with a focus on prevention of diseases.  My goal is to help you feel better and have a better quality of life.  I am a certified BioTE practitioner that provides BHRT, also known as bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, which naturally balances the hormones of women and men, designed to correct the problems of hormone imbalance that will help protect your heart and brain from debilitating diseases as well as age better.  I am one of three skilled nurse practitioners at Med Care of Adairsville.  Come see us!

name: Med Spa of Flower Mound
bio: Cheryl Smitherman was born and raised in Fort Worth Texas where she resides with her husband of 29 years and her three children. She obtained a Bachelor of Arts Degree in English from Texas Womans University in 1989 and was a public-school educator for 7 years. She achieved a Bachelor of Science in Nursing Degree from Texas Womans University in 1998 and has 17 years of experience as a Labor & Delivery Nurse, Womens Services Educator, and Labor & Delivery Manager.  She obtained her Doctor of Nursing Practice Degree from Baylor University and was licensed as a Certified Nurse-Midwife by the Texas Board of Nursing in 2013. She became an Associate Professor in the undergraduate program at Baylor Universitys Louise Herrington School of Nursing and opened a prenatal clinic in Arlington for underprivileged women where she provided prenatal care. She came to Denton County in 2014 where she has provided midwifery and womens health care for the past three years.Cheryl comes to North Texas Obstetrics & Gynecology Associates with a wealth of experience and a passion for womens health.  As an educator and Certified Nurse-Midwife, she believes in a collaborative partnership with her patients and their families. Her mission is to support women and their families through education and informed decision-making.  Her belief is that all women deserve quality health care across the lifespan, and her mission is to provide patient-supported health care in a compassionate and healing environment.

name: Med Vital Walk In Lab and Clinic
bio: Jessica DaCosta is a Family Nurse Practitioner, board-certified by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners (AANP) and licensed by the state of Florida to provide family-centered healthcare to patients of all ages. Her scope of practice encompasses health promotion and wellness, disease prevention and diagnosis and management of health care problems.She began her nursing career in the emergency room caring for trauma patients and has practiced in the ER since. She has accumulated nearly thirteen years of nursing experience and education in critical emergency\/trauma care and trauma education. She is also nationally Board Certified in Emergency Medicine by the Emergency Nurses Association (ENA\/CEN) as well as an active Trauma Nursing Core Curriculum Instructor (TNCC- Instructor). Jessica, possesses strong skills and takes pride in providing the best health care possible to all of her patients. She also strives to acquire a comprehensive evaluation of every patient by taking time to listen and understand each patients particular needs.

name: MedChic, LLC
bio: We are the first doctor's office in the Condado area to specialize in women's healthcare. Our comprehensive practice offers a full range of Maternal Health and Family Medicine services for women of all ages. We provide personalized treatment by appointment.SERVICES:Womens HealthPreventive MedicineMaternal CareComprehensive MedicinePreoperative EvaluationAdolescent HealthMenopauseHormonal DisordersContraception Minor SurgeryComplementary MedicineModern MedicineABOUT THE DOCTOR:Dr. Heileene Torres-Colberg, is the sole proprietor and medical director of MEDChic, LLC.After completing her medicine studies and then, her 3 years training of residence in Family Medicine in Puerto Rico, she was conferred with the Academic Achievement Award and was certified as Diplomate of the American Board of Family Medicine in 2014. She also completed her first fellowship in Maternal Child Health\/Surgical Obstetrics and a second fellowship in Faculty Development; both in the city of Chicago, IL. Recently, precisely for her academic and professional accomplishments, Dr. Torres-Colberg was recognized by her medical school with the 2016 Notable Alumna Award.Besides her private practice, she works and is a Faculty Member of the Auxilio Mutuo Hospital and an Associated Professor at the Family Medicine Residency of the University of Puerto Rico. She also maintains her activities as an Obstetrics Provider in the Chicago area. Dr. Torres-Colberg holds positions in the Board of Directors of the Academy of Family Physicians of Puerto Rico as in the Womens Health Society of Puerto Rico.Dr. Heileene Torres-Colberg has made very clear her social and public health commitment concerning women and maternal issues. It is this dedication towards her profession and medical education what has made Dr. Torres-Colberg a local and international speaker, as well as a medical consultant, mostly, in womens health related issues. One of her goals is to teach, be part and achieve the best and newest comprehensive medicine for women, her patients and for Puerto Rico.

name: MEDI Care Clinics
bio: Philip Hamby FNP joined FMNTX in January 2013. In addition to being a provider, Philip serves as the Clinical Director with a focus on business development. Philip brings with him over a decade of healthcare experience. Philip grew up in small town Mississippi where he graduated early, at the age of 17, to enlist in the United States Marine Corps where he served five years on active duty. His duty took him as far away as Okinawa, Japan and as close as NAS JRB Fort Worth, where he met the love of his life and settled down. After the Corps, Philip attended the University of Texas at Arlington, receiving his Bachelors of Science in Nursing. Philips nursing career spanned many settings, including: emergency, post op recovery and correctional. Philip returned to school to earn his Masters of Science in Nursing, with a focus in Family Nurse Practitioner, from Texas Womans University. Philip continues his service to our country as a Commissioned Officer in the Air Force Reserve.Philip enjoys primary care because it affords the opportunity to have a long, meaningful relationship with his patients. Philip strives to live by the ethos of treating others as he would want to be treated. In addition to primary care, Philip has a real heart for those suffering with substance and chemical addiction. In 2010, Philip helped to found a local residential treatment center in DFW. He currently serves as the Director of Nursing for Soteria, LLC (www.soteriacare.com), an Intensive Outpatient Program (IOP) in Arlington, TX.Philip resides in North Fort Worth with his wife, three kids, Great Dane and Siamese. When not working or with family, Philip enjoys spending time with his church family, exercising, reading books, watching movies, hunting and golfing.Education:1.B.S.N. from The University of Texas at Arlington2.M.S.N. from Texas Womans University

name: MEDI Care Clinics
bio: Medicine is about the people, not the profits.James G. Purgason, MD retired from the United States Navy Reserves in 2004 with 21 years of combined service, and has been in practice in Ft. Worth for 10 years before moving his practice to Denton, TX. In 2008, he was named Top Doc by Fort Worth, Texas Magazine.Family Medicine of North Texas client base is continually expanding because of Dr. Purgasons dedication to building intimate, long-term family relationships one patient at a time. It is his commitment to provide every patient with state-of-the-art health care in a friendly, clean, and comfortable environment.When hes not at his practice, Dr. Purgason can be found gardening, restoring cars and boats, and spending time with his family and four cats.Education:1.B.S. from The University of Texas at Austin2.M.D. from The University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio3.Family medicine and family practice internships completed at the Pensacola Naval Hospital4.Residency completed at Family Practice, John Peter Smith Hospital

name: MEDI Care Clinics
bio: Casey Jamison, WHNP, FNP joined FMNTX in August of 2015. She was raised in Dallas and attended nursing school at the University of Oklahoma. After 6 years of Trauma ICU experience she attended Texas Womans University where she obtained her Womens Health Nurse Practitioner. She then obtained her Family Nurse Practitioner from South University in 2016. Casey resides in Little Elm with her husband and two children. She enjoys traveling, reading, and spending time with her family. She believes in the importance of taking care of her patients as a whole and providing preventative medicine as often as possible.Education: B.S.N. from The University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center M.S.N. from Texas Womans University Post masters certificate from South UniversityAffiliations: Texas Nurse Practitioners North Texas Nurse Practitioners

name: Medical Aesthetics of New England, PC
bio: Dr. Walter is a clinical instructor for the University of Massachusetts Medical School, a fellow of the American Society of Laser Medicine and Surgery and the American Board of Emergency Medicine, a member of the Faculty of the American College of Emergency Medicine, and a member of the American Society of Laser Medicine and Surgery and American Academy of Cosmetic Physicians, as well as the American College of Emergency Physicians. He has received specialized aesthetic training at the Anti-Aging Institute in Texas, as well as being trained in VASER techniques at the Advanced Body Institute in Colorado. A graduate of the Tufts University School of Medicine, Dr. Walter is also board certified in Emergency Medicine and works in the Emergency Department at Emerson Hospital in Concord.A former president, board member and national councilor of the Massachusetts College of Emergency Physicians, he has received their Distinguished Service Award, President Award and Vanguard Award in recognition of his service to patients and emergency medicine. Dr. Walter has also worked extensively with the state Department of Public Health to help implement the Massachusetts Stroke Service Center Program for hospitals and improve emergency medical services across the state. Dr. Walter is proud to be offering BioTE for hormone optimization.

name: Medical Aesthetics of New England, PC
bio: Stephanie Liatsis, RN is our Chief Aesthetician, and is one of the top injectors of BOTOX and fillers in New England. Her superior technique is recognized by Allergan (the makers of BOTOX and JUVDERM); who selected her to train physicians and nurses from all over the country in advanced applications for BOTOX and cosmetic fillers. In addition to specialty training in Emergency Medicine and her dermatological and aesthetic experience, Stephanie has trained at the Esthetic Skin Institute for Physicians and Nurses in Ft. Lauderdale, FL. A member of the Dermatology Nurses Association and AMEN (Association of Medical Esthetic Nurses), she is also a member of the American Society of Laser Medicine and Surgery.
