Before attending OUHSC, she received her bachelors degree in 2007 from Oklahoma State University in Nutritional Sciences where she graduated cum laude.  She is a member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants as well as the Oklahoma Academy of Physician Assistants.It is a privilege to work with women of all ages and to have the opportunity to provide care from adolescence to menopause, she adds.  I feel that our practice provides the important combination of intellect and empathy that is so vital to good medicine.\",",",47cacc8e2e5f2940"

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio: Christina (Tina) Telcocci, PA-C, graduated from the Physician Associate program at the University Of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center here in Oklahoma City. She earned her Master of Health Science degree with Special Distinction.Prior to joining Optimal Health Associates in 2009, Tina worked ten years for a premier interventional pain management practice. Her empathy and understanding of patients needs is all too personal.In March of 2006, I was diagnosed with Stage IIB Hodgkins Lymphoma, she recounts. I was blessed to have access to wonderful medical care at every stage of my diagnosis and treatment. I cannot even imagine going through such a frightening and uncertain time without all the excellent physicians, nurses, and other medical staff I came into contact during that time.After six months of chemotherapy and two months of radiation treatment, Tina was cancer free. But shed gained a lesson for her lifes work.My personal goal is to treat each of my patients with the same respect and compassion that I received and that they deserve. I want to provide each with guidance and understanding of their medical conditions.Whether you are facing a life-threatening cancer, a life changing event such as menopause, a fertility issue, or you come in for a normal healthcare maintenance visit, I would like to help provide a calm, stable, and safe environment for you to discuss your concerns.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio: Patricia Hall, PA-C, earned her masters degree in Health Science as a Physician Assistant at the University of Oklahoma Physician Associate Program. She is board certified and scored in the 99th percentile on the national certification exam. Prior to beginning her graduate program, she earned her bachelors degree from the University of Oklahoma in Nutritional Science.Prior to joining Optimal Health Associates in 2013, she worked as a Family Practice Physician Assistant in Akron, Ohio. Because of my experience in the primary care setting, she says, I enjoy seeing our patients whose needs may fall beyond the realm of gynecology.My goal is to work with patients to address their concerns and help them reach their emotional and physical goals all while providing the most comfortable environment possible, she adds. I feel very fortunate to be a part of such a caring, knowledgeable healthcare team that strives to provide each patient with the highest level of care and respect.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio: Benjamin J. Barenberg, M.D., FACOG, is a board certified Gynecologic Surgeon and fellowship trained Urogynecologist. Dr. Barenberg assists both male and female patients in need of advanced hormone replacement therapy including BHRT Pellet Therapy. Dr. Barenberg earned his medical degree from the University of Texas in Galveston and completed his residency training at Loyola University Medical Center in Chicago, IL. He furthered his education with fellowship training in Female Pelvic Medicine and Reconstructive Surgery at the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center in Oklahoma City. During fellowship training, Dr. Barenberg received his Masters of Science degree in Clinical and Translational Research from the University of Oklahoma Graduate College. Dr. Barenberg is the founder of Genesis Wellness which is Oklahomas first and only concierge wellness service. Genesis Wellness takes pride in restoring patients hormonal and physical balance in the privacy and comfort of their home.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio: Dr. Sandler obtained a B.S. in Zoology from the University of Michigan. He completed his medical school education at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio. His residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology was performed at the University of California, San Diego.Dr. Sandler developed the bulk of his clinical experience practicing at the Scripps Clinic Medical Group in La Jolla, CA. He is Board Certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.In the past 15 years, Dr. Sandler, led Shared Wellness, LP. Shared Wellness helps physicians and other health care providers incorporate wellness and weight loss programs into their practices. His deep experience advocating health and wellness, including, as well as a desire to provide complete healthcare for women, including advanced hormone replacement therapy, within the specialty of Gynecology, led to his decision to join Optimal Health Associates.Dr. Sandler and his wife, Susan, have three children, Tasha, Ben and Jeremy, and they cant get enough of their granddaughter, Harper. While they enjoy theater, music and travel, their most rewarding activity is spending time together as a family on the slopes skiing and on the beach.

name: Optimal Hormone Health
bio: Born and raised in Salt Lake City Utah, Monica Olsen Bell knew early on that she wanted to dedicate herself to a rewarding career in medicine. In 1998 Monica graduated from Westminster College with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.  Monica continued her education at the University of Utah,  graduating Magna Cum Laude, with a doctorate in Nursing Practice. As a board-certified Acute Care Nurse Practitioner she is committed to working with patients in a collaborative therapeutic relationship. Monica specializes in bio-identical hormone therapy individually tailored for men and women to achieve optimal health. Utilizing the most recent medical literature to responsibly guide treatment, Monica dedicates herself to patient safety first, which remains the cornerstone of her preventative clinical practice.

name: Optimal Hormone Health & Wellness
bio: Michelle is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner.  She obtained her Master of Science Degree in Nursing from the University of Texas Health Science Center-Houston, where she graduated with honors. She is a member of the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners, North Harris Montgomery Advanced Practice Nurse Society, and Sigma Theta Tau Nursing Honor Society. Michelles passion is health and wellness and she tries to live what she teaches. As an avid fitness enthusiast, she enjoys weight training, boxing classes with her husband, and any type of activity with her three children. She encourages patients to be pro-active with their health and focuses on health promotion and disease prevention through diet and exercise, making healthy, balanced lifestyle choices, and through the use of bio-identical hormones. Michelle believes in treating the whole patient and will always dig a little deeper to help patients get to the source of their symptoms. She also encourages the use of dietary supplements to help restore balance and support the bodys natural ability to heal itself.  Michelle is continually expanding her knowledge in the area of age management preventative medicine by attending specialty conferences, symposiums, and training seminars.

name: Optimized Wellness
bio: Jordan Bernard is a family nurse practitioner board certified through the American Association of Nurse Practitioners. She graduated with a Masters of Science in Nursing from the University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences in 2015. Jordan currently works in regenerative and physical medicine and is excited to expand her professional expertise to hormone pellet therapy. She enjoys partnering with patients to improve their health and knowledge base. Jordan has previously worked in primary care implementing innovated projects relating to Transitional Care Management in Tyler, Texas prior to moving to Colorado.

bio: Kevin Morgan is a native of Port Arthur, Texas and has lived in Bridge City, Texas for the past 28 years.  He graduated from Lamar University with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.  He worked in Critical Care with pediatric and adult patients for 5 years, the last three of which were also spent obtaining a Masters degree in Nursing and specializing in Family Medicine.  He has spent the last ten years also specializing in Nutrition and Weight Loss and is highly sought after in this area of expertise.  When he is not helping his clients achieve their best, Kevin enjoys doing anything artistic which includes bodybuilding, playing guitar, singing, drawing, and gourmet cooking.

bio: Dr. Rebeca Velzquez, has a medical practice in Hato Rey, Puerto Rico. She specializes in Obstetrics and Gynecology and has over 10 years of experience in the field of medicine. Dr. Velzquez obtained her medical degree in 2004 in Universidad Central del Caribe. She completed her Ob-Gyn Residency program in 2008 at the San Juan City Hospital in Centro Medico. Is affiliated with the Ashford Prebisterian Hospital in Condado area and is an attending physician in Clinics for the Women in Fajardo, Cupey and Trujillo Alto area. She is a certified doula physician since 2015. Dr. Velazquez specializes in bio-identical hormone replacement, having attended conferences and obtained certification in bio-identical hormone replacement, pellet therapy. Dr. Rebecca Velazquez is accepting new patients at her co-founded medical office and practice location: Optimum OB\/Gyn, 268 Hato Rey Center Bldg. suite 1000 Ave. Ponce de Leon, Hato Rey PR. name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio: With more than 20 years of experience performing gynecological surgeries, Dr. Marc L. Winter has invested his energy in developing and offering less invasive procedures to his patients. Not only does Dr. Winter see referrals from outside Orange Coast Women`s Medical Group, but he also gives lectures, publishes papers and instructs other doctors on minimally invasive gynecological techniques.Dr. Winter has been practicing in Laguna Hills since 1989. He specializes in robotic surgery and has experience performing complex hysterectomies, myomectomies and sacrocolpopexies with the use of the da vinci robotic surgical system. He has worked extensively with the use of graft materials to enhance pelvic reconstructive surgery (treating bladder, rectal, uterine, and vaginal prolapse).Dr. Marc Winter has performed over 400 robotic surgeries at Saddleback Memorial Medical Center (SMMC) in Laguna Hills. Dr. Winter and SMMC have been designated one of only twenty-three epicenters, or national training sites in robotic gynecologic surgery for Intuitive Surgical, the maker of the da Vinci robot. At the SMMC training ground, Dr. Marc Winter teaches surgeons nationwide the latest in robotic surgical techniques. Patients can expect the most advanced care and excellent clinical outcomes.Dr. Winter completed his residency training at the University of California at Irvine College of Medicine where he is currently an Assistant Clinical Professor.Professional Affiliations:Diplomat, American Board of Obstetrics and GynecologyFellow, American College of Obstetricians and GynecologistsAmerican Association of Gynecological LaparoscopistsSociety of Laparoendoscopic SurgeonsOrange County OB\/GYN Society

bio: Carolyn is certified in womens health and has been a Nurse Practitioner at OCWMG since 1994.  She decided to specialize in womens health when she was a Registered Nurse (RN) in Labor and Delivery and felt she could help women in good times and in difficult times.

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio: Beverly has a Masters degree in nursing and has been a Nurse Practitioner since 1983.  She has been with the practice since the beginning, working for OCWMG doctors May and Audell since 1990. She is proud to share that Dr. Audell and Dr. May delivered her children at Saddleback Memorial.Beverly takes pleasure in treating, educating and interacting with patients. She enjoys working with outstanding doctors, nurses and staff. If you dont love your job, then why are you doing it?Her hobbies include socializing and going to lunch with good friends.

bio: Dr. Raffo received a Bachelor of Science degree from Agnes Scott College (a small women`s college in Georgia). She received her medical degree from University of California, Irvine, where she also completed her residency training. Dr. Raffo has been in practice with Orange Coast Women`s Medical Group since 1997.\The excitement and diversity of obstetrics and gynecology is what attracted me to this specialty. I find it very rewarding to help my patients with their individual medical needs. Part of my responsibility as a physician is to provide education and options to my patients. I believe each patient has the right to be the ultimate decision maker in her own care. This can only be achieved if she understands the necessary information and has a mutually trusting relationship with her doctor.\"\"The rewards of educating and caring for women of all ages are immense. It is a privilege to be part of that unforgettable moment in a womans life as she gives birth. The close relationships I have formed with many of my patients bring me great satisfaction. bio: Dr. O`Toole feels that the patient should play an active role in making decisions of her own medical care. She is especially noted for her interest in women`s health, including but not limited to infertility, osteoporosis, and menopause, as well as the challenge of obstetrics.After earning her Bachelor of Science degree in Zoology at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona, she attended the University of Health Sciences, at Chicago Medical School. She received her medical degree in 1985, and then completed an internship in internal medicine at L.A. County USC Medical Center and her residency in Obstetrics & Gynecology at the Women`s Hospital at L.A. County USC Medical Center. Following the completion of her residency, Dr. O`Toole moved to Orange County and began her Obstetrics and Gynecology practice. Board certified in obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. O`Toole is a member of the North American Menopause Society.Born in Greenville, Mississippi, Dr. O`Toole had the opportunity to live in different areas all over the United States, as well as the Orient while she was growing up. Dr. O`Toole is now married and has a son and a daughter. She enjoys many activities and sports, including running, swimming, and skiing. She is an avid reader and loves to bake. She looks forward to living in the Orange County area, caring for her patients, for many years.Professional Affiliations:Diplomate, American Board of Obstetrics and GynecologyFellow, American College of Obstetricians and GynecologistsNorth American Menopause Society

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio: Enjoying all aspects of women's health, Teresa Whitman became board certified as an NP after completing the Women's Health Care Nurse Practitioner Program at Harbor\/UCLA. Previously working in labor and delivery at Long Beach Memorial Hospital, Teresa then began working as an NP in women's health, practicing for the last seventeen years in Newport Beach. Finding ultrasound to be a significant asset, Teresa also earned certification in obstetric and gynecologic ultrasound.Teresa's interests include adolescent health, pregnancy and recurrent pregnancy loss, routine gynecologic care including annual examinations and contraception, and menopause concerns including traditional and \bio-identical\" hormone replacement therapy and maintenance of healthy bone density.Living in Orange County with her husband Mike
doctor_email: Teresa enjoys family ski trips with their two children and gardening."

name: Orange Coast OBGYN
bio: Caroline Conner, M.D.Dr. Caroline Conner earned her medical degree at University of Texas at Houston, and completed her residency at University of California, Irvine. Dr. Conner is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a member of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology and the American Medical Association.She provides a full range of obstetrical and gynecological care and specializes in minimally invasive surgical techniques including robotic surgery and endometrial ablations. She has been practicing in the Orange County area for approximately ten years.Her patients like her non-intimidating nature and feel comfortable discussing their personal needs in her office. She is a native Texan and likes spending time experiencing the outdoors. She also enjoys taking care of her young daughter Aspen.

name: Oregon Derma Center
bio: Dr. Jessica Black graduated from the National College of Naturopathic Medicine She has published The Anti-inflammation Diet and Recipe Book and co-authored Living with Crohns and Colitis; A comprehensive Naturopathics Guide to Health and Wellness with Dede Cummings.  Dr. Black specializes in womens medicine including natural hormone balancing and childhood wellness.  Because of her thirst of knowledge she continues to study and research treatment ideas to improve peoples health and became a certified BioTE physician.  She takes pride in educating her patients about pellet therapy and why its so safe and effective.  Come see Dr. Black and start feeling your best today!

name: Oregon Derma Center
bio: Dr. Jason Black did his medical training at the National College of Naturopathic Medicine.  He specializes in treating many complex pain conditions and focuses on restoring the health of damage tissue resulting from injuries or inflammation.  Dr. Jason is skilled in multiple therapies to reduce pain including Prolotherapy and trained in effective injection therapy for fat reduction and aesthetic procedures.  Dr. Jason knows the importance of hormonal balance to pain patients, providing optimal health care and disease prevention.  He knows pellet therapy is the superior delivery method to feel your best.  Becoming a certified BioTE physician, Dr. Jason is not just adding years to your life, but adding life to your years.

name: Orthopedic & Physical Medicine Associates
bio: David W. Duffner, MD, MBA David W. Duffner, MD, MBA, is an orthopedic surgeon specializing in spinal surgery with 28 years of experience. Dr. Duffner currently serves as medical director of the Spine Services Program and has been recognized as a Top Doctor in his specialty for the past six years in a row by Castle Connolly Medical Ltd., conductor of a peer-nominated survey as published in Palm Springs Life.Prior to moving to the desert, Dr. Duffner served as president of a large orthopedic group in Tyler, Texas which he founded in 1990. Drawing on his successful practice and experience in Texas, he established the Spine Patient Assessment (SPA) program at ICON  a multidisciplinary approach in a peer-reviewed setting to provide treatment decision support and documentation for optimal patient care and risk management.Operating on a philosophy that for most spine conditions surgery is the last resort, not the first, Dr. Duffner places a key emphasis on proper patient selection and optimizing the right treatment for a given patient. He has a phrase he likes to share with surgery patients: The decision is more important than the incision.While Dr. Duffner enjoys the complexities and technical aspects of spine surgery, he is most concerned with how the patient feels  how has the surgery positively impacted their life. To this end, he has extensive experience in patient outcome studies and has been instrumental in improving outcome tracking at ICON  proudly reporting five years of data meeting or exceeding national database benchmarks.Dr. Duffner earned his Medical Degree from the University of Oklahoma. He served his residency in orthopedics at Texas A&M. He also has received fellowship training in adult reconstructive orthopedics at the University of Basel in Switzerland. Additionally, he earned a Master of Business Administration degree from the University of Houston.Dr. Duffner is a fellow of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons (AAOS), a founding member of the North American Spine Society (NASS), and a member of the Riverside County Medical Association. He has published and lectured extensively on reconstructive orthopedics and spine surgery.At Desert Regional Medical Center, Dr. Duffner currently serves as chief of orthopedics and chairman of the Bioethics Committee. Previously, he served as chair of the Department of Surgery for four years and was a member of Desert Regional Medical Centers Governing Board for three years.Dr. Duffner and his wife, Jana, live in Palm Springs. In his leisure time, he enjoys golf, hiking and other outdoor sports.

name: Orthopedic Specialists
bio: Dr. Williams is originally from a small town in rural Maine. He attended Syracuse University for pre-med and then Medical School at the Kirksville College of Osteopathic Medicine in Kirksville, Missouri. After graduation, he did a whole year internship at Suncoast Hospital in Largo, then completed his Orthopedic residency in Queens, NY. After residency, Dr. Williams completed a one year fellowship in Hand and Microvascular Surgery at the University of Miami, Jackson Memorial Hospital in Miami, Florida.Dr. Williams provides treatment options in all areas of general orthopedics and fracture problems. He provides many non-operative as well as operative treatment options for a vast number of accident related injuries. Dr. Williams has had additional training for the treatment of non-surgical neck and back related problems. Dr. Williams currently serves as the Chief of Surgery at Helen Ellis Memorial Hospital in Tarpon Springs, and the Chief of Orthopedics at Trinity Surgery Center in New Port Richey. In addition, he is a speaker for Ascension Orthopedics for surgeries to replace the MCP, PIP and CMC joints in the hand.Dr. Williams, his wife Samantha, and their children live in Tarpon Springs with their pets. In his spare time, he enjoys working on automobiles, watching motor sports, ice hockey and football games.

name: Ovation Med Spa
bio: Dr. Asra Oberoi has been in practice since 1996. She opened one of the first medical spas in the Houston area and is passionate about helping people look and feel their best, through the latest non-invasive cosmetic treatments and hormone optimization programs. Dr. Oberoi is fully trained and certified as a BioTE specialist for bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, and is the Medical Director for Ovation Med Spa in Houston, TX, recently nominated as one of the Best Aesthetic Practices in the USA. In addition to BioTE bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, Ovation Med Spa offers the latest advances in non-surgical Skin Rejuvenation and Body Contouring, Laser Hair Removal, as well as standards like Botox, and cosmetic fillers.   Educational Background Undergraduate  Texas Tech University, Lubbock, TX 1984-1987, B.S. ChemistryGraduate  Texas Tech University, Lubbock, TX 1987-1989, M.S Cell and Molecular BiologyMedical School  Texas Tech University School of Medicine, Lubbock, TX 1989-1993, Medical DoctorInternal Medicine Residency -Scott and White Memorial Hospital, Temple, TX, 1993-1996Endocrinology Fellowship  The University of Texas Medical Branch, Galveston, TX 1996-1998 Organizations Texas Medical AssociationIndo-American FoundationAmerican Academy of Aesthetic MedicineAmerican Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine

name: Oxford Obstetrics & Gynecology Associates
bio: Julie Harper received her undergraduate degree from the University of Mississippi with a B.A. in psychology. She continued her education and received her medical degree from the University of Tennessee Health Science Center in Memphis. While in medical school, she was awarded Alumni Achievement Award in Clinical Medicine in 1999 for excellence in medical arts and sciences and dedication to the highest ethical and professional standards. Dr. Harper completed her residency in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Alabama in Birmingham. She was elected Administrative Chief Resident in 2002-2003 and received the Charles E. Flowers Jr. Award for Excellence in Teaching in 2000-2001. Previously, Julie Harper was in private practice with Memphis Obstetrics and Gynecology Associates and served on the DeSoto Surgery Center Medical Advisory Board. Dr. Harper is a board certified Fellow of ACOG.Hobbies: Dr. Harper's hobbies include keeping up with her two college kids and two younger kids, who are involved in travel swim, baseball, soccer and basketball.  Family: Dr. Harper is married to James D. Harper, an attorney with Harper Whitwell. They have four children.  Interesting Fact: She is a third-generation physician. Her mother and grandfather both graduated from UTHSH and practiced medicine together in Memphis. Favorite thing about her job: She enjoys working with women through all aspects of their life, from the adolescent stage to menopausal years. She says, I am privileged to get to partner with them in health and starting their families along this journey.

name: P.L. Allen Health and Wellness Center
bio: Dr. Patrick Allen, a native Texan, began a successful private practice in Fort Worth and North Richland Hills Texas in 1999. He is on staff at North Hills Hospital and Harris HEB Hospital. Dr. Allen is a graduate of the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio; he completed his residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Oklahoma University of Health Science. He is a Diplomat in the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and Board Certified and a fellow in the American College for Obstetrics and Gynecology. He is very dedicated to providing exceptional healthcare to women. He is very excited to have brought the DaVinci Robot to North Hills Hospital for less invasive gynecologic surgery.Dr. Allen and his wife have three daughters and live In Keller Texas. They are very active in their parish church. He is a competitive Master swimmer and a guitar enthusiast.

name: P.L. Allen Health and Wellness Center
bio: Marie T. Murphy, CNM was born and raised in Ireland. After receiving her RN license she moved to Scotland where she graduated in 1983 as a Midwife. Marie used her education to pursue her love of travel, first practicing Midwifery in Abu Dhabi, then in London, UK, Perth, Australia and in Saudi Arabia. For Marie working in such diverse areas of the world helped enrich her understanding and build a respect for the cultural traditions of women around the world.Marie is a very unique person; her professional and personal life experiences have given her a wonderful ability to relate to women in every stage of their lives. She has worked in private practice since 1997. In 2000, she joined Dr. Patrick Allen in his OB\/GYN practice located in North Richland Hills and Fort Worth.Being a Certified Nurses Midwife, Marie provides all aspects of in office gynecological and prenatal care with special emphasis on patient education, health and wellness promotion and disease prevention.

name: P5 Performance
bio: Dr. Ravi B Patel is a board certified physician in Internal Medicine. He also completed his specialization in Geriatric Medicine in New York City and moved back home to Dallas in 2005. He has been recognized in D Magazine as one of the Best Doctors in Dallas for three consecutive years. Dr. Patel has served on multiple hospital committees as well as Chief of Staff for an acute rehabilitation hospital for two years. He has also participated in a medical mission trip to Honduras to provide care to over 1,400 patients.His journey as a physician, practicing in various hospitals from New York City to Texas, has exposed him to the challenges of the current care of the patient. Dr. Patel has seen that the ultimate care of the patient is by looking beyond traditional boundaries and providing a multidisciplinary approach. His inspiration comes from seeing the value of getting a head start in proper healthcare from a younger age by embracing a more preventative lifestyle.Dr. Patel strives to be a role model to his patients, emphasizing good health along with proper nutrition and fitness. As such, he leads a very active life and loves playing baseball and soccer with his children. Dr. Patel has also found fun ways to incorporate fitness into his familys daily routine and you will often find his children at the gym with him

name: Pacific Hair Institute
bio: Dr. Elliott grew up in Omaha, Nebraska, the fourth generation in medicine. He attended Johns Hopkins University Undergraduate, University of Nebraska College of Medicine for medical school, and University of Iowa Hospitals, Department of Dermatology for Residency.He was trained in hair transplantation in 1971, while a Dermatology Resident. Over the years, he invented many things which advanced the process of hair transplantation. He has always been at the forefront of the latest technology. You can rest assured that the techniques used at Pacific Hair have been and will continue to be the latest technology available.Dr. Elliott is a Diplomate of the American Board of Hair Restoration Surgery. He began his interest in Endocrinology by reading the Merck Manual in his grandfathers office (the Endocrinology section) when he was 9 years old. He has always been fascinated by the many effects that the endocrine system has in controlling the human body.He was trained in bioidentical hormone replacement by Dr. Neal Rouzier in the 1990s. He has practiced bioidentical hormone replacement for his patients since. He has recently been additionally certified by Dr. Gary Donovitzs BioTE company for the insertion of pellets containing either testosterone or Estradiol, which are an improved method of delivering constant blood levels of hormones (which exceed the ability of hormones delivered through the skin).Dr. Elliott lives in Orange County and is the founder of Pacific Hair Institute and Pacific Longevity Institute.

name: Paradise Wellness
bio: Dr. Kristine Sarna is a board-certified Family Physician specializing in wellness and anti-aging services. She is an Arizona native, having completed her medical school education at the University of Arizona in Tucson and her Family Practice Residency at Good Samaritan Hospital in Phoenix. Dr. Sarna is also Board Certified in Integrative Holistic Medicine and holds certification in Medical Acupuncture from UCLA School of Medicine. Dr. Sarna enjoys treating patients of all ages. She believes in providing natural options for our patients to improve their health, including vitamin and nutraceutical therapies as well as acupuncture and lifestyle modifications. Dr. Sarna has specialized training in Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy for men and women. Dr. Sarna is co-owner of Norterra Family Medicine and Paradise Medspa & Wellness, our sister office, providing cosmetic skin care and wellness services.

name: Paragon Infusion Centers
bio: Michelle Chien has had a passion for helping people with their medical needs. She earned her Master of Science degree in Nursing from Texas Womans University.  She is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner. She believes in preventative health care and has a special interest in bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.  She currently works for Paragon Innovative Infusion Center, which is known to provide a high quality level of patient care. She takes her time to understand her patients concerns and explain the medical terms in understandable way. She enjoys traveling and spending time with her family.

name: Paramount Medical Consulting Inc.
bio: Dr. Jorge R. Brothers specializes in urology, and has over 46 years of experience in the field of medicine. He was born and raised in Mexico City. He graduated from The National University of Mexico with his medical degree in 1970. He completed two years of residency in general surgery at the University of Louisville in Kentucky and then transferred to Tulane in New Orleans to complete four years of urology training. He is a member of the American Urological Association and Texas Medical Association. Dr. Brothers has been an active urologist in the Lubbock community over 30 years. He is affiliated with numerous hospitals in Lubbock. He continues to accept new urology patients. He offers the no scalpel vasectomy. His special interests include hormone replacement therapy and prostate cancer. His passion for years has been implanting penile prosthesis. Stacy Brothers was born in Lubbock, Texas. She graduated as a registered nurse with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center in 1995. Her nursing career began in urology  where she became board certified in urology at the registered nurse level. As her passion for urology evolved she decided to advance her education. Stacy graduated with a Master of Science in Nursing and from the Family Nurse Practitioner program from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center. She is certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.  She is the president of the West Texas chapter of Society of Urologic Nurses and Associates. Her passion for years has been helping couples with hormone replacement therapy. The Brothers are happily married with one daughter who cheers on varsity for the Lubbock Cooper Pirates, cheers on platinum at Raider Extreme, and dances on diamonds for Studio X. Jorge and Stacy enjoy spending time with family and friends, cooking, and travelling.

name: Park Ridge Pain Specialists
bio: Ernesto Padron, MD earned his medical degree at UIC. He then completed a two year internship in General Surgery, residency in Anesthesia as well as a Fellowship in Pain Management. Dr. Padron Specializes in Pain Management concentrating in Lumbar, Thoracic and Cervical areas of the spine. He also treats most joint pain, using a wide variety of minimally invasive interventions.Dr. Padron recently opened his own clinic, Park Ridge Pain Specialists, establishing his business in an easy to reach location and looks forward to treating new patients while continuing with follow-ups for his existing clientele.Dr. Padron's \bedside manner\" is professional
doctor_email: engaging and sought after as a practitioner of his specialty. And he is bilingual Spanish so there is no misunderstanding his intervention techniques or expectations as a result of his treatments."

name: Parker Square Family Practice
address: 19641 E. Parker Square Dr., Suite E
bio: Hi, Im Dr. Jana Jacobs and I have maintained a medical practice in the Parker area since 1997. My interests have been in womens health care and preventative medicine since becoming a licensed physician in 1992. After obtaining my medical degree from the University of Health Sciences, Kansas City, I completed the family medicine residency at Truman Medical Center in 1995, also in Kansas City. I have two daughters. Kristin lives in Denver and is studying to be a radiology technician, and Jennifer lives in California with her children Jack & Ella. If you ask me about my grandchildren you will get an earful!After years of prescribing pills for fatigue, depression, insomnia, muscle aches and pains, night sweats, low libido, low energy and lack of mental focus I was excited to learn of a very successful alternative approach with BioTE. As we age, the natural hormones we have decline and we begin to predictably suffer from the results of this. After becoming certified in the BioTE Method of hormone replacement, I am now offering this therapy to my patients. The pellet method of hormone replacement has been used and studied for many decades and is a safe and effective treatment option for both women and men. The science and experience behind the BioTE Method offers a better quality of life for all who suffer from the above mentioned symptoms. I would be happy to discuss this with you to see if you would be a good candidate for this treatment option. A simple questionnaire and blood test is all that is needed to see if you would benefit from this therapy. I hope to see you soon!
