name: Parker Weight Loss
bio: Lisa Hammond is a Family Nurse Practitioner with several years of experience.  Lisa worked as an RN for over 13 years and then pursued a Masters degree in 2012 from the University of South Alabama.  Lisa has experience in Endocrinology, Internal Medicine, Weight loss\/Hormone therapy and Aesthetics. One of Lisas passions is aesthetics\/cosmetics and loves helping clients build their confidence.  Her other passion is helping clients find their optimal wellness by balancing hormones.  Lisa is married with four children.  When Lisa is not working, you will find her spending time with her family, working out, or on the slopes snowboarding in the mountains.

name: Parker Weight Loss
bio: Jordan Bernard is a family nurse practitioner board certified through the American Association of Nurse Practitioners. She graduated with a Masters of Science in Nursing from the University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences in 2015. Jordan currently works in regenerative and physical medicine and is excited to expand her professional expertise to hormone pellet therapy. She enjoys partnering with patients to improve their health and knowledge base. Jordan has previously worked in primary care implementing innovated projects relating to Transitional Care Management in Tyler, Texas prior to moving to Colorado.

name: Parkway Primary Care
bio: Ann-Marie is from southeast, Texas and moved to the Austin area 10 years ago.  She has had an R.N. degree since 1996 and NP since 2006.  She enjoys sports and is a die hard Houston Texan fan.  She plays softball for fun and enjoys traveling and nature.  She has one teenage son and is excited about joining the Parkway Primary Care family of providers.

name: Path of Life Functional Medicine
bio: Path of Life Functional Medicine is located in Avila Beach, California along the Bob Jones trail. We are a functional medicine practice with a team of doctors and health coaches who specialize in finding the root cause of your disease and don't just treat the symptoms.

name: Patricia Stafford MD
bio: Patricia A. Stafford, M.D. is known as a physician with a passion for helping clients achieve optimal wellness, with a focus on nutrition, physical fitness, hormone balancing, and positive lifestyle changes. Dr. Stafford has undertaken extensive training in the area of bio-identical hormone restoration. She is a certified practitioner of SottoPelle hormone pellet therapy and is also certified in The Wiley Protocol for biomimetic hormone therapy. Through her professional training and personal health commitment, Dr. Stafford guides and inspires each patient to achieve optimum health, using natural approaches to achieve a healthful balanced life. Dr. Stafford completed the two-year Fellowship in Integrative Medicine through the University of Arizona under the direction of internationally known author and health expert Andrew Weil, M.D. Dr. Stafford was one of less than 50 physicians chosen from candidates around the world to enter the program in 2001, graduating in 2003. Furthermore, Dr. Stafford has completed the Helms Medical Institute training in Medical Acupuncture and the Mei Zen Cosmetic Acupuncture training for face and neck as well as weight loss and fertility. She is also working toward her certification as a personal trainer through the American College of Sports Medicine. Prior to opening Wellness ReSolutions, Dr. Stafford provided services as a respected specialist in breast and women's imaging at Women's Imaging & Wellness of Dublin. She completed her residency at the University of Cincinnati in Diagnostic Radiology, serving as Chief Resident in her final year. She also completed an internship in Internal Medicine at The Christ Hospital in Cincinnati as well as attending the University of Cincinnati for her undergraduate education.

name: Patt Internal Medicine
bio: Dr. Madhavi R Patt is a Johns Hopkins trained, board-certified internist with more than seventeen years of clinical practice experience in adult medicine and preventive care. She is one of a few North American Menopause Society Certified Practitioners in Colorado. Dr. Patt has had extensive practice experience in both internal medicine and urgent care clinics. She has also dedicated part of her professional career to improving chronic disease management and primary care. She is dedicated to her patients and if theres a concern, she will find a solution

name: Paul Howard MD
bio: Dr. Howard attained his Medical Degree from The Oklahoma University School of Medicine in 1970.From 1971 through 1974, Dr. Howard worked as The Chief of Flight Medicine at Edward's Air Force Base, the Famous Flight Training Center located in California's Mojave Desert and received Commendations from The Secretary of The Air Force, Department of Surgery for his work and Service.He served his Internship and Surgical Residency at Kansas City General Hospital and Medical Center from 1970 until 1977.In July 1977 Dr. Howard began his Residency for Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery, finishing in 1979 and earning Full Board Certification in 1981.Member ASPS (American Society of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery), The American Board of Medical Specialties, Tulsa Surgical Society & Tulsa Medical Society.

name: Paul Millmann MD
bio: Dr Millmann has been in private practice in Sherman, Tx serving the citizens of Grayson County for the last 25 years. He graduated medical school in 1981 and served his residency in Family Medicine at JFK Medical Center in New Jersey and was elected Chief Resident.Dr Millmann belongs to the Texas Medical Assoc and is a Fellow in the American Academy of Family Physicians. He is currently Board Certified in Family Medicine. He is also a member of the Texas Academy of Family Physicians.Dr Millmann has been honored with the Physicians Recognition Award from the AMA and is listed in America's Top Family Doctors.He was recently chosen Texoma Best Family Physcian in 2009.

name: Paula Snokhous PA
bio: Coming soon!

name: Peaks of Health Metabolic Medical Center
bio: Dr. Tracie Leonhardt grew up as a member of the local community and is a graduate of Largo High School. She graduated from Southeastern University (now known as Nova University) in 1992, completed her internship at Suncoast Hospital in Largo, and, completed her Residency in Emergency Medicine at Midwestern University in Chicago, Illinois in 1996. Dr Leonhardt began her 14 year tenure in emergency medicine at Northside Hospital in St. Petersburg, Florida in 1996, where she earned the titles of Associate Medical Director of the Emergency Department, Chairperson of the Emergency Department and then Medical Director of the Emergency Department.  During her tenure in the Emergency Department, Dr. Leonhardt also worked with medical control for over 10 years as an online medical control physician, in which she worked closely with our first responders in the field while enhancing their education.  Dr. Leonhardt was honored to present a lecture to the American Osteopathic Society in New Orleans in 2010 on the subject of Type II Diabetes.

name: Peaks of Health Metabolic Medical Center
bio: Dr. Miranda Giusti earned her medical degree from Lake Erie College of Osteopathic Medicine in Bradenton, Florida after obtaining her bachelors in Biology from the State University of New York at Geneseo. Now finishing her Internal Medicine Residency at Largo Medical Center, she is looking to pursue a fellowship in Integrative Medicine afterwards. As an officer of the Young Physicians Organization for Pinellas County Osteopathic Medical Society (PCOMS), she leads 14 medical students each year on a medical mission trip to Jamaica aiding the rural community of Treasure Beach. Educating her patients on the importance of a healthy lifestyle centered around exercise, nutrition, and stress reduction, is a passion Dr. Giusti pursues with all her patients. When not at work she enjoys dancing, running, paddle boarding, weight training, physique competitions, and traveling the world to experience various cultures

name: Perlow Medical Corporation
bio: Hello! My name is Dr. Rebecca Lee Perlow. To distinguish myself from my husband most patients call me Dr. Rebecca. This is pretty much my usual garb, exactly how youll see me in the office. I was an RN( Registered Nurse) graduate of Los Angeles County\/ University of Southern California Nursing school and started my first job as an RN at Tarzana hospital on January 16, 1982.I am proud to state I was a Labor & Delivery Nurse:) I worked nights and went to school by day to get my degree in Cellular and Molecular Biology from California State University Northridge in 1987. I attended Western University Health Sciences in Pomona to achieve my Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine degree in 1993. Yes, Osteopaths do surgery and write prescriptions. I attended Kaiser Permanente on Sunset Boulevard in Los Angeles, California from 1993 to 1997.I am board certified in Obstetrics & Gynecology from the American Congress of Obstetricians & Gynecologists. I remain a Fellow of the American Congress of Obstetrics & Gynecology which is what the FACOG behind my name stands for. I meet all the annual requirements to maintain certification ( called MOC) by the ACOG .I am former Vice-Chief of Obstetrics & Gynecology at what is now Providence Tarzana Medical Center. I returned to my hospital in 1997 to join my husband in our private practice. It is the only hospital I have privileges for other than out patient surgery centers.I absolutely love my job, it was worth every second of advanced education to be able to care of you all!Dennis Leonard Perlow graduated from University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA) with a Bachelors Degree in Psychology in 1959. He attended the University of California Irvine, California College of Medicine achieving his MD in 1963. He completed his Residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology from 1963 to 1967.He served as a Lieutentant Commander in the United States Navy in Pensacola, Florida from 1967 to 1969. He became Board Certified in Obstetrics & Gynecology in 1969 (also ACOG). Moved back to California in 1969 to his own private practice where he has been ever since.He served as Chief of Obstetrics & Gynecology at Tarzana hospital from 1985 to 1987. He began the first Chart & Peer Review committee at Tarzana, well before the Joint Commission on Accreditation of Hospitals (JCAHO) required it. He loves all animals, especially dogs, cats, birds, and pretty much any animal will come to him unprovoked.

name: Perlow Medical Corporation
bio: Adina Gregor is a family nurse practitioner who is board certified by the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC), which a subsidiary of the American Nurses Association (ANA). She graduated with her Masters of Science as a family nurse practitioner from Maryville University in 2017. Adina is currently a member of the California Association for Nurse Practitioners (CANP) and works as a nurse practitioner at Perlow Medical Cooperation. She has worked as a Labor and Delivery RN for the last 13 years and has a passion for womens health. As a heath care provider, Adina empowers her patients by educating them and giving them the tools to take control of their personal health. She is a firm believer that prevention is key, and she incorporates all different approaches to optimize her patients health physically as well as mentally.  Adina believes in building a long-lasting relationship with her patients built on trust. She seeks a comprehensive evaluation of every patient by taking the time to listen and understand his or her individual needs. Her true desire is to enhance a positive healing experience and instill confidence for those in need by using a combination of holistic and medical treatments.

name: Personalized Health & Wellness PA
bio: Dr. Fleming feels that his role as a doctor is to educate the patient about all her alternatives to leading a healthy life. Through listening to the unique nature of each patients history, he can provide treatment choices which complement the particular lifestyle of that person.In order to achieve optimum quality of life for the women for whom he cares, he is able to provide advanced surgical care for a variety of gynecologic problems such as abnormal bleeding and falling of pelvic organs. His experience allows him to practice not only routine and high risk obstetrics, but advanced laparoscopic surgery and management of complex medical and surgical problems. He is skilled in da Vinci robotic surgery and serves as a trainer for other physicians in this technique.A passionate interest is specific testing for hormone deficiencies that may prevent women from living life to the fullest. Many women feel fatigue, mind fog, poor sleeping and loss of sexual desire. This feeling can often be addressed by treating deficiencies of the ovaries, thyroid glands, and adrenal glands that occur with time. Many women find return of vitality and sense of well-being from these treatments.Dr. Fleming is a native Texan. He supported himself through college and medical school by working a variety of jobs including rancher, carpenter, and teacher. He began his training in general surgery but changed to obstetrics and gynecology when he realized this area was his true calling.When not working, he enjoys sports, cooking, outdoor activities, and spending time with his wife, Jeanine, and their three daughters.

name: Personalized Health & Wellness PA
bio: Balancing the ability to diagnosis and treat disease with taking the time to listen and communicate defines the role of an obstetrician\/gynecologist. This is the philosophy of Dr. Jacoby whose mission is to educate and empower his patients while providing excellent medical care for routine and high-risk obstetrics, adolescent\/adult gynecology, advanced laparoscopy, preventive medicine\/nutrition, and sexual dysfunction.In his comprehensive treatment of women, Dr. Jacoby understands the need to consider relationships with significant others. He recognizes the importance and the challenges for the couple in achieving and maintaining effective communication and satisfying intimacy. Dr. Jacoby established the Center for Sexual Enrichment to provide medical and psychological assessment and treatment in order to promote sexual health and to improve the capacity for intimacy.Dr. Jacoby is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, a member of the American Association of Sex Educators, Counselors, and Therapists and has served as Chief of the Department of Ob\/Gyn at the Medical Center of Plano.For leisure, Dr. Jacoby enjoys spending time with his wife and two boys.

name: Personalized Wellness
bio: Dr. Ken Cleveland is Co-founder and Medical Director of Remedy True Health. Originally from Alabama and a graduate of the Alabama School of Medicine, Dr. Cleveland moved to Jackson, MS in 1996 to complete his surgical training at the University of Mississippi. After practicing General Surgery for 11 years, Dr. Cleveland retired from General Surgery to start Remedy True Health, a unique clinic to the Jackson area, offering Bio-identical Hormone Replacement Therapy, Weight Loss and Aesthetics. The goal of Dr. Cleveland and Remedy True Health is to help people prevent disease and give them the opportunity to live a longer, happier life.

name: Personalized Wellness
bio: WORK EXPERIENCE NORTHSTAR ANESTHESIA, Jackson, Mississippi Staff Anesthesiologist    |   Jan 2016 - Mar 2018 EDUCATION ANNA-JONESBORO COMMUNITY, Anna, Illinois SOUTHERN ILLINOIS UNIVERSITY, Carbondale, Illinois B.A. KIRKSVILLE COLLEGE OF OSTEOPATHIC MEDICINE, Kirksville, Missouri D.O. DAVENPORT MEDICAL CENTER, Davenport , Iowa Rotating Internship UMMC, Jackson, Mississippi Anethesiology Residency ADDITIONAL SKILLS PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE SURGICAL ANESTHESIA ASSOCIATES, Jackson, Mississippi Staff Anesthesiologist    |   Jul 1995 - Jan 2016 CREDENTIALS AND LICENSES Board Certified Anesthesiologist 1995-present

name: Phoenix Men's Health Center
bio: Dr. Jean-Luc Le Provost received his medical degree from the Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine, a formally accredited naturopathic medical school in Tempe, Arizona.  He received additional training in homeopathy, botanical medicine, acupuncture, hormone replacement therapy, Chelation, IV nutrient therapy and nutrition to complement his medical training.Prior to medical school, Dr. Le Provost was the manager and owner of successful personal training and nutritional guidance practice in Tucson, Arizona. It was through the close relationships he developed with his clientele that he was inspired to delve into wellness further in the study of holistic health.Originally from Nevada, Dr. Le Provost moved to Arizona to attend the University of Arizona where he received his Bachelor of Science in Dietetics and Nutritional Sciences.Dr. Le Provosts extensive background in nutrition, personal training, pharmaceuticals, and alternative medical therapies provides his patients with the most update knowledge in the world of integrative medicine.His goal is to improve your quality of life and help you live your life to its fullest potential.

name: Phoenix Women's Center
bio: Dr Lovelady completed her OB\/GYN residency at Detroit Medical Center in 2001. Dr. Lovelady has been in private practice and had joined a community health center in Atlanta. She also practiced at an Indian Health Services' location in Oklahoma. Dr. Lovelady joined with Dr. Burse to form Phoenix Women's Center, P.C. in 2006.

name: Phoenix Women's Center
bio: Dr. Burse has been practicing OB\/GYN in metropolitan Atlanta since she completed her residency at Wayne State University School of Medicine, Detroit Medical Center in 1995. Most recently, she had worked part-time on an as needed basis at a community health center in Atlanta. Now Dr. Burse dedicates all her professional time to providing women excellent healthcare at Phoenix Women's Center, P.C.

name: Physician's Care of Greenwood
bio: Founded in 2003 by Dr. Jed Graham with the vision of creating a medical practice that treats every patient with dignity and first-rate care. The clinical and office staff at Physicians Care are trained and exceptionally friendly. We understand that for many, visiting a doctor can be a stressful experience. Our comfortable surroundings and compassionate medical professionals will ease your fears. \Come let us provide care to you and your family\"Jed Graham M.D. earned a Bachelor of Business Management from Phoenix University in 1992 and received his Medical Doctorate Degree from Ross University of Medicine in 1999. He successfully completed his family medicine residency at Self Regional Healthcare in 2003. Dr. Graham is board certified by the American Board of Family Medicine. Dr. Graham serves as Medical Director of Abbeville Nursing Home and is certified by the Dept of Health and Human Services Center for Substance Abuse to provide treatment to patients struggling with opioid addiction. Jed enjoys research
doctor_email: fishing and golf. He is married to Michele and together they have 3 children."

name: Physician's Center for Beauty
bio: Dr. Sean Maguire is a plastic surgeon who specializes in cosmetic surgery of the face, breast and entire body. After he graduated Magna Cum Laude from the University of Louisville School of Medicine, he became Board-Certified in head and neck surgery. He then completed a residency in Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery at the University of Cincinnati and a fellowship in Aesthetic Plastic Surgery and Laser Surgery with Dr. Larry Schlesinger in Maui, Hawaii.His keen eye for aesthetics, and his training and experience, have enabled him to master what is, indeed, the artistry of cosmetic surgery. Dr. Maguire is widely-praised for performing procedures such as:Blepharoplasty (eyelid surgery)Rhytidectomy (face lift) Brow liftRhinoplasty (nose reshaping)Breast and body contouringLiposculptingLaser Skin ResurfacingTo request a consultation with Dr. Maguire call (502) 897-7546 to schedule your visit.

name: Physician's Center for Beauty
bio: Kaitlyn Hicks is a born and raised Louisvillian and a nurse practitioner at Physicians Center for Beauty. Prior to becoming a nurse practitioner, she began working as a nurse in 2011 in critical care and then a trauma emergency room. After she graduated from Bellarmine University with her family nurse practitioner degree and became certified with the American Association of Nurse Practitioners, she worked in dermatology and cosmetic research prior to joining the team at Physicians Center for Beauty. Kaitlyn is passionate about caring for a persons complete wellbeing, focusing on a more holistic approach to care, which is what was so appealing to her about the BioTE program. Outside of the office, Kaitlyns loves include spending time with her loved ones, traveling the world, blogging, trying new restaurants and playing tennis.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Dr. Turner is a Board Certified OB\/GYN. He received his Bachelor of Science degree from Messiah College in central Pennsylvania. He attended medical school at the Pennsylvania State University College of Medicine. He joined the Navy during his second year of medical school and was stationed in Portsmouth, Virginia after graduation. He remained in Portsmouth after graduation from residency as an attending physician for 3 years. While there he served as the GYN Department Head. After completing his obligation to the Navy, he moved to Hamilton AL where he practiced a full component of OB\/Gyn Medicine. Dr. Turner specializes in Obstetrics and Gynecology, with a special interest in Urogynecologic issues. Dr. Turner performs many advanced laparoscopic procedures as well as in-office cystoscopy, hysteroscopy, and complex urodynamics. In the future, Dr. Turner is hoping to add bioidentical hormone replacement therapy to his offered services.Dr. Turner has been married to his beautiful wife for thirteen years and they now have four children, three biological and one adopted child. Dr. Turner is actively involved in his home Church, The Ramp in Hamilton AL.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Please see attached pic and  Dr. Otey's bio below.  He is attending training this weekend.  After graduation from Union University in Jackson TN, Dr. Otey received his Doctorate of Medicine at East Tennessee State University Quillen College of Medicine in Johnson City, TN.  He then went on to complete a general surgery internship at East Tennessee State University.  A four year residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology followed at The University of Tennessee in Knoxville, TN where he received the Excellence in Teaching Award.In 1997, Dr. Otey began his practice at Physicians and Surgeons.  He specializes in general obstetrics and gynecology, menopausal symptoms, urinary incontinence, vaginal reconstructive surgery, infertility and high risk obstetrics.  Dr. Otey is excited to provide both robotic and laparoscopic minimally invasive surgical procedures including hysterectomy, removal of ovaries, and treatment of fibroids.  He is especially interested in vaginal reparative surgery for pelvic organ prolapse and incontinence issues.Dr. Otey is an active member of the medical staff at Gilmore Memorial Regional Medical Center, Amory, MS and Baptist Memorial Hospital, Columbus, MS.  He currently serves as Chairman of the Obstetrics\/Gynecology Surgical Committee at Gilmore Memorial Regional Medical Center.  Dr. Otey is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists and a member of the Society of Pelvic Reconstructive Surgeons.When not with a patient, you will find Dr. Otey enjoying time with his family, church, running or cycling.Dr. Otey accepts new patients and referrals for all aspects of womens health care at both the Amory and Columbus clinic locations and looks forward to serving you.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Dr. Duke J Wood joined Physicians & Surgeons Clinic in the summer of 2002.  A Louisiana native, he easily found roots in North East Mississippi.Dr. Wood is a Board Certified Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists.  He is a member of the Honorary Medical Societies; Sigma Sigma Phi and Alpha Omega Alpha.  After completing his undergraduate at Oklahoma State University he attended medical school at Oklahoma State University College of Osteopathic Medicine.Dr. Wood received the Surgery Department Award and award for Clinical Excellence in his graduating class.  He was residency trained at Akron General Medical Center and served as the Executive Chief Resident of his Program.  He currently serves as the Medical Director of Physicians & Surgeons Clinic.Dr. Wood specializes in general obstetrics and gynecology, routine and high risk pregnancies, infertility, menopause, gynecologic abnormalities, laparoscopic and vaginal surgery.  His special interests lie in fostering a unique and memorable labor and delivery experience.When not operating or delivering babies, Dr. Wood can be found outside on his ATV with his children, working out at the local gym, or spending time at Bethel Apostolic Church.Dr. Wood is currently accepting new patients and referrals at both our Amory and Columbus clinics.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Alison received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing at Mississippi University for Women in 1999. At this time she also completed all degree requirements for Paralegal Studies. In 2008, Alison completed her Master of Science Degree, graduating with honors, in the Family Nurse Practitioner program. She is Board Certified in Mississippi and has national certification through American Nurses Credentialing Center.In addition to being an exceptionally talented Nurse Practitioner, her professional activities include membership in Sigma Theta Tau (International Honor Society of Nursing); and Phi Kappa Phi, an honor society dedicated to the recognition and promotion of academic excellence.Alison has a passion for the teaching aspect of womens health, with a strong interest in preventative care and adolescent\/young adult needs.A native of Lowndes County, Alison is married with two children. She is active in her local community and volunteers weekly at her childrens school. Alison enjoys family time, boating and sporting events.Alison warmly welcomes all former patients and is excited to receive new patients with any OB\/Gyn issue. Alison accepts all referrals for Obstetrics and Gynecologic care.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Dr. Chaney is a Board Certified OB\/GYN. Dr. Chaney received his Bachelor of Science degree from Mississippi State University in 1981. He attended medical school at the University of Mississippi Medical Center, graduating in 1985. He began his practice with Physicians and Surgeons Clinic after completing his residency at Vanderbilt University Medical Center in 1989.Dr. Chaney specializes in Obstetrics and Gynecology, focusing on Robotic Surgery, Pelvic Repair, Urinary Incontinence Surgery, general gynecology, Infertility and general obstetrics. He is a Diplomat of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is also a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. He is the Past Chair of the Mississippi Section of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists and is also an active member of Mississippi State Medical Association.Dr. Chaney is very involved within his local community. In his spare time, Dr. Chaney enjoys spending time with his family, fishing, reading and exercising.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: For Columbus native Pamela Lacy, it was all about where babies come from. Apparently, an informative book on the topic made an impression on Lacy as a young girl. Thats when she decided to become a doctor.After graduation from Mississippi State University, she received a doctorate from the Medical College of Pennsylvania Hahnemann School of Medicine and completed her residency at UTSW Parkland Memorial Hospital in Dallas. She was involved in research of abnormal Pap smears in pregnancy and received the Peggy J. Walley Medicus Award in 2006 as an outstanding resident. Dr. Lacy began her practice with Physicians and Surgeons Clinic in 2006 as the clinics first female OB\/GYN. Dr. Lacy specializes in high risk pregnancies, infertility, gynecological abnormalities, menopause, preventive medicine and laparoscopic surgery, including robotic surgery.She is currently Medical Director of Obstetrics at Baptist Memorial Hospital. She is a member of Baptist System Obstetrics Advisory Group. The Advisory Group reviews hospital policies throughout the Baptist system and works toward improvements in patient care.Dr. Lacy is an expert spokesperson on Midmorning with Aundrea, where she gives medical advice and information on womens healthcare issues.Dr. Lacy is a Fellow of American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: For Columbus native Pamela Lacy, it was all about where babies come from. Apparently, an informative book on the topic made an impression on Lacy as a young girl. Thats when she decided to become a doctor.After graduation from Mississippi State University, she received a doctorate from the Medical College of Pennsylvania Hahnemann School of Medicine and completed her residency at UTSW Parkland Memorial Hospital in Dallas. She was involved in research of abnormal Pap smears in pregnancy and received the Peggy J. Walley Medicus Award in 2006 as an outstanding resident. Dr. Lacy began her practice with Physicians and Surgeons Clinic in 2006 as the clinics first female OB\/GYN. Dr. Lacy specializes in high risk pregnancies, infertility, gynecological abnormalities, menopause, preventive medicine and laparoscopic surgery, including robotic surgery.She is currently Medical Director of Obstetrics at Baptist Memorial Hospital. She is a member of Baptist System Obstetrics Advisory Group. The Advisory Group reviews hospital policies throughout the Baptist system and works toward improvements in patient care.Dr. Lacy is an expert spokesperson on Midmorning with Aundrea, where she gives medical advice and information on womens healthcare issues.Dr. Lacy is a Fellow of American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: Physicians & Surgeons Clinic
bio: Originally from Amory, Mississippi, Dr. Laura Marion received her medical degree from the University of MS Medical Center in Jackson, Mississippi. She went on to complete her training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Memorial Health University Medical Center in Savannah, Georgia in July 2016.During residency she received numerous honors, including the 2016 Most Outstanding Resident in Obstetrics in Gynecology, as well as third place in Memorials hospital-wide Research Day with her individual research entitled, Cost Effectiveness Analysis of Cord Blood Sampling Using ACOG Guidelines. While a resident, Dr. Marion was actively involved with ACOG and served as Georgias Junior Fellow Chair and Vice Chair, attending annual district and clinical scientific meetings, as well as coordinating the Georgia section of District IVs service project of unused OR supplies for medical missions.Dr. Marion enjoys seeing women of all ages and feels that she can give guidance and be a positive role model to adolescents and young adults. She also enjoys preventative medicine, in-office procedures and routine, as well as, high-risk obstetrical care.Dr. Marion is also very active; She is an avid runner and loves volunteer opportunities. Each year she looks forward to participating in her favorite event, Joy Proman annual prom event for special needs individuals in the community.

name: Physicians Center for Weight Loss and Age Management
Physioage Medical Group
bio: Dr. Raffaele received his B.A. in philosophy from Princeton University and his MD from Hahnemann University Medical School in 1989. Dr. Raffaele did his residency at The New York Hospital\/Cornell University Medical Center and was formerly a clinical assistant professor of medicine at Dartmouth Medical School while in practice at the Hitchcock Clinic. Dr. Raffaele is a member of the American College of Physicians, is board certified in internal medicine, and is a diplomat of the American Board of Anti-Aging Medicine. In 1995 Dr. Raffaele began researching and developing a scientifically-based treatment program and co-founded PhysioAge Medical Group. Since 1997 Dr. Raffaele has been exclusively focused on anti-aging medicine and bioidentical hormone replacement therapy.

name: Pinnacle Internal Medicine & Headache Care
address: 6320 W Union Hills Dr. Ste A-180
bio: Dr. Christine Harter received her MD in 1985 from Johns Hopkins. She did her residency at Hopkins Bayview Medical Center in Baltimore Maryland and has practiced internal medicine and headache care for over 30 years. She has been working with adults of all ages, male and female, 18 and up, including hormonal problems, for the past 30 years, and has a reputation for treating the whole person, not just numbers, and being a great listener, as well as a great internal medicine doctor. She started her own internal medicine practice in the Phoenix area in 2008; it is a small, personalized practice where her staff knows each patient personally. Shannon Kuettel, PA-C is also a certified practitioner in our practice and graduated with a 3.95 GPA at A.T. Still University, and also is known for being a great listener and meticulous practitioner.All the staff here at Pinnacle Internal Medicine and Headache Care look forward to seeing you to optimize your wellbeing with bio-identical hormone treatment.

name: Pinnacle Internal Medicine & Headache Care
address: 6320 W Union Hills Dr. Ste A-180

name: Pinnacle Restorative Health, PLLC
bio: Katie Anderson, FNP joined FMNTX in January 2014. Katie was born and raised in Lubbock, Texas where she graduated from Texas Tech University with a Bachelors Degree in Nursing. Katie brings 5 years of experience starting in Fort Worth at John Peter Smith Hospital with a focus in trauma and critical care and continued in a critical care setting at Presbyterian Hospital of Denton. Katie resides in south Denton and enjoys reading, jogging, hiking, snowboarding, watching movies and spending time with her family. Katie has a passion for healthy living, nutrition, and exercise. She enjoys helping people and creates dynamic partnerships that can help them achieve a satisfying and healthy lifestyle. She understands making the changes that result in continuing and long-term health benefits require long-term support. Katie has a great appreciation and understands the role nutrition and exercise play in the state and progression of disease as well as the factors that support or hinder health behavior changes.Education: B.S.N. from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center M.S.N. from Texas Womans UniversityAffiliations: Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners Texas Nurse Practitioners North Texas Nurse Practitioners

name: Pioneer Health Care
bio: Vishnu Maya Upadhyay owns and operates Pioneer Healthcare Clinic. She is a certified family and womens Health Nurse Practitioner. In Pioneer Healthcare Clinic with Vishnu Maya Upadhyay you and your family are truly in safe and caring hands.She first received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from Raj Kumari Amrit Kaur, College of Nursing in New Delhi, India. Afterwards, she obtained her Certification in a Womens Health Care Nurse Practitioner from UT Southwestern Medical Center in Dallas, Texas and a Master of Science in Nursing with a major in Family Nurse Practitioner from Texas Womans University in Dallas, Texas.Vishnu Maya Upadhyays qualifications for operating her own clinic stems from her strong background in creating, implementing and administering patient care in family and womens health clinics over the period of 13 years. She is highly skilled and equipped with knowledge in providing healthcare. She pocesses detailed knowledge of HIPAA, OSHA and JCAHO accreditation and has excellent time management and supervisory skills to direct the support staff, medical assistant externs, nursing and nurse practitioner students.Vishnu Upadhyay has several honors under her belt. In 2007, she was a recipient of an Outstanding Nurse Practitioner Student Scholarship by the North Texas Nurse Practitioners organization. In 2007-2008, she was also a recipient of an Advanced Education Nursing Traineeship by the Department of Health and Human Services.Her vast experience in overall medical family and womens health practice has lead her to author a professional paper entitled Assessment of Grief after Miscarriage using Perinatal Bereavement Scale for Advanced Nurse PractitionersVisit Pioneer Health Care clinic and get to know her better

name: Pittman Moore MD
bio: Dr Pittman D Moore is a board certified on\/Gyn who graduated from the University of Arkansasfor Medical Sciences in 2004 and completed his residency at UAMS in obstetrics andgynecology in 2008. From there he went on to establish Moore Surgical Arts and Gynecology inLittle Rock, Arkansas where he practices gynecology and specializes in advanced laparoscopicsurgical technique, vaginal aesthetic surgeries, laser surgery and bioidentical hormonereplacement therapy. Dr Moore is also owner of Harmony Health Medical Spa in Clarksville,Arkansas and partner in Revive Lifestyle Medicine located in Little Rock, Arkansas. He is afellow of the American College of Obstetrics & Gynecology, member of the American College ofCosmetic Surgery, American Academy of Gynecologic Laparoscopy, International Society ofCosmetogynecology, and the American Urogynecologic Society. He has been married for 10years to his wife Casey and has 5 children Cole, Emma, Davis, Dylan, and Jack. He enjoys alllake activities, hunting, fishing and working out.

name: Plano Wellness Center PLLC
bio: Dr. Marlene Diaz received her BA in 1987 from the University of Texas at Austin and her MD in 1991 from the University of Texas, Southwestern Medical School in Dallas, TX.  She completed her residency at Parkland Memorial Hospital in Dallas, TX.  She is Board Certified with the American Board of OB\/GYN.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Heather Bellanger is a partner at Plano Womens Healthcare.  She enjoys all aspects of being a physician from routine gynecological care to pregnancy, childbirth and beyond.   Dr. Bellanger has a focus on minimally invasive procedures including robotic surgery.  She is affiliated with The Medical Center of Plano and Forest Park Medical Center.  Dr. Bellanger received her medical degree from the University of Texas, Southwestern Medical Center and stayed in Dallas to complete her residency at University of Texas Southwestern, Parkland Memorial Hospital.  She is Board Certified with the American Board of OB\/GYN.  In her off time she enjoys spending time with her husband and two children, Madeleine and Preston.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Julie DaVolio is a partner of Plano Women's Healthcare.  She received her BA in 1988 from the University of California-San Diego and her MD in 1993 from Tulane University School of Medicine in New Orleans, LA.  She completed her residency at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio, TX.  She is Board Certified with the American Board of OB\/GYN.  Dr DaVolio currently practices at the Medical Center of Plano as well as Forest Park Medical Center of Frisco. Dr. DaVolio, along with her husband Michael, live in Plano with their two children.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Amy K. Mos is a partner of Plano Womens Healthcare, which is the largest female-only practice serving Collin and Dallas County. Dr. Mos enjoys providing personalized and compassionate healthcare to women during all phases of their lives with a special focus on high-risk obstetrics and minimally invasive procedures.  She currently practices at Forest Park Medical Center of Frisco and the Medical Center of Plano where she is serving as the Chief of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  Dr. Mos received her training in Obstetrics\/Gynecology at UT Southwestern, Parkland Memorial Hospital and attended medical school at Texas Tech University School of Medicine. Both Dr. Mos, and her husband, Daniel, grew up in Plano and enjoy spending their time with their children, Dylan and Sophie.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Marlene Diaz received her BA in 1987 from the University of Texas at Austin and her MD in 1991 from the University of Texas, Southwestern Medical School in Dallas, TX.  She completed her residency at Parkland Memorial Hospital in Dallas, TX.  She is Board Certified with the American Board of OB\/GYN.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Arlene Jacobs graduated from Tulane University School of Medicine in 1985. Dr. Jacobs is licensed to practice medicine in the state of Texas. Specializing in the field of Obstetrics & Gynecology, Dr. Jacobs is prepared to provide comprehensive care for the reproductive system in women. Obstetrics is the term for women's care during the prenatal and pregnant states, while gynecology covers care for general women's health in a non-pregnant state.

name: Plano Women's Healthcare
bio: Margaurette T. Walsh is board-certified by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants and is a member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants. She graduated with a Masters Degree in Physician Assistant Studies from Massachusetts College of Pharmacy and Health Sciences in Boston and gained experience in Internal Medicine, General Surgery, Emergency Medicine and Urgent Care while training and working at hospitals in the Boston area. Mrs. Walshs desire to have a positive impact on the lives of others led her to a career in the medical field. She moved to Texas from New Hampshire with her husband Kevin and two fun loving children Bralyen, 4, and Kiana 1 1\/2 years old. She brings to Plano Women's Healthcare her strong clinical skills centered around patients feelings, symptoms and overall well-being. She is dedicated to providing options and encouragement to patients so that they may achieve their healthy potential.

name: Plastic Surgery Clinic of Northwest Arkansas
Plastic Surgery Institute & Spa
bio: After completing undergraduate and medical school, Dr. Ceydeli continued his medical training at the University of Medicine & Dentistry of New Jersey, where he obtained a Master of Science degree in Anatomy, Cell Biology & Injury Sciences. His extensive research on the basic science of cell biology and scarless wound healing won him numerous awards, including one from the American College of Surgeons and another from the Association for Academic Surgery. His graduation thesis was published in the prestigious medical journal, Shock. In addition to his basic science research, he completed a Clinical Trauma Fellowship at New Jersey Medical School under the supervision of Dr. John H. Siegel, a pioneer in Trauma Surgery in the United States.Subsequently, he started his General Surgery training at New York Methodist Hospital, where he also served as a chief resident. During his General Surgery residency, his interest in Plastic & Reconstructive Surgery grew. His creativity and surgical skills were recognized by the American Society for Aesthetic Plastic Surgery (ASAPS), and he was invited to present a novel aesthetic breast surgery procedure he invented at that societys annual meeting when he was a third-year General Surgical resident. His contributions to Cosmetic Surgery were also recognized by the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery, and his paper received the Best Resident Paper of the Year award.Upon completion of his General Surgery training, Dr. Ceydeli started his Plastic & Reconstructive Surgery residency at the Medical College of Georgia. He contributed numerous articles to the Plastic Surgery literature, continued to present his innovative techniques at national meetings, and continued to receive accolades during his Plastic Surgery training.Dr. Ceydeli was selected by Consumers Research Council of America for inclusion in the 2007 Guide to Americas Top Plastic Surgeons and has been honored in multiple editions of Whos Who in America, which named him one of the emerging leaders in Healthcare and Medicine. He is one of only a handful of plastic surgeons in Northwest Florida to be double board certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery and the American Board of Surgery.After finishing his Plastic Surgery training, Dr. Ceydeli also completed a prestigious Aesthetic Fellowship in Honolulu, Hawaii with the legendary Dr. Robert Flowers. Dr. Ceydeli is one of the few Plastic Surgeons in the country to be accepted to this program. His fellowship in Hawaii mainly focused on Facial Aesthetic Surgery and Asian Plastic Surgery.After completing this fellowship, Dr. Ceydeli settled in Panama City Beach, on Floridas Emerald Coast. His double board certification in plastic surgery and his advanced cosmetic surgery training with Dr. Flowers have made him uniquely qualified to pioneer numerous innovative procedures, both invasive and non-invasive, since his move to Northwest Florida.Working in concert with his mentor Dr. Flowers, Dr. Ceydeli invented the revolutionary MAG-5 facial rejuvenation procedure, a breakthrough that changed the concept of aesthetic facial surgery the world over. They co-authored the landmark article about MAG-5 in the prestigious plastic surgery journal, Clinics in Plastic Surgery. They presented and taught this innovative technique at numerous national and international scientific meetings. Plastic surgeons from every corner of the globe flew in to watch and learn this technique.When facial structures start migrating southward due to the effects of gravity and aging, the MAG-5 procedure relocates them to the north, for the most natural and long lasting results. This is in contrast to most other facial procedures, such as the facelift, which pulls the face to the east and west, instead of lifting it northward where it belongs. The term facelift is actually a misnomer. Since the incisions made for this procedure are next to the ears, the facelift technique can only pull the face towards to ears, which in most cases gives the face an unnatural, tight look and does not address aging-related changes around the eyes and brows, or the cheek tissue itself. MAG-5, on the other hand, lifts the eyebrows, rejuvenates the lower eyelids by restoring its youthful almond shape, and lifts all the cheek tissue (not the skin alone), returning it to its original location. And, unlike those of a facelift, the MAG-5 incisions are invisible. There are only two incisions, one on the hair-bearing scalp, and another tiny incision under the eyelid. There are no incisions and thus no scars in front of the ear. This novel MAG-5 concept provides natural and longer lasting results.One of the other innovative techniques Dr. Ceydeli learned from his work with Dr. Flowers is Valentine Mouth Rejuvenation. Again, due to the effects of gravity and aging, the corners of the mouth turn downward, giving the face a sad, frowning look. Many physicians think that this problem can be corrected by injecting soft tissue fillers or doing fat transfers. However, without addressing the down-turned mouth corners, injections alone only make matters worse. Patients often end up with the swollen sausage lips and lack of lip definition we have become all too familiar with. Dr. Ceydeli addresses the aging mouth by lifting the corners of the lips with a heart-shaped design flap (a small office procedure performed under local anesthesia), which gives the face a happy, pleasant look. He uses soft tissue fillers not to enlarge the lips, but to redefine them. His advanced chemical peel technique and\/or state-of-the-art laser treatment further eliminates wrinkles around the lips and improves skin texture around the mouth area. The entire procedure is performed in the office under local anesthesia and takes less than an hour, giving the lips and mouth region an instant aesthetic improvement with natural results. No unnaturally inflated sausage lips  guaranteed.Dr. Ceydeli is the only plastic surgeon in the region performing liposuction-assisted short-scar breast lifts and reductions. Although he has made improvements to traditional breast lift\/reduction techniques (inferior pedicle Wise-pattern breast lift\/reduction) and published articles on the subject, he now exclusively uses the liposuction-assisted short scar-breast lift\/reduction technique for all breast lift and reduction cases, no matter how big or sagging the breast. With this technique, he minimizes unsightly scars beneath the breast, and more importantly, sculpts a beautiful, round, uplifted breast with longer lasting results than traditional breast lift\/reduction techniques.Dr. Ceydelis tummy tucks (abdominoplasties) are also different from the rest. They are not simply removing excess skin and fat, but rather toning and sculpting the abdomen with a sexy waistline, creating a natural innie belly button, and placing the incisions low enough that scars are invisible even with the lowest-cut bikini bottom.In addition to his innovative and unique approaches to face, breast, and body, Dr. Ceydeli established the first advanced follicular unit hair transplantation center in the region, resulting in numerous happy patients. The newest techniques in hair transplant require a team approach, and Dr. Ceydelis hair transplant center is staffed with some of the best Bosley-trained hair technicians in the country with many years of experience.Despite his advanced surgical training and background, Dr. Ceydeli has pioneered some of the most advanced non-invasive skin rejuvenation techniques in Floridas Panhandle. He adapted the True Blood skin rejuvenation technique to his practice. This technique uses the patients own blood to rejuvenate the skin. Platelet-rich plasma, or PRP rich in growth factors and stem cell markers is obtained from the patients blood and reinjected back under the skin, thus stimulating skin cells to repair and refresh themselves. Since the persons own blood is used, this is an absolutely safe approach, and the device used to obtain the PRP is FDA-approved. Even though this innovative technique is popular in Europe and has been featured in the US media, Dr. Ceydeli is still the only physician in Northwest Florida and one of the very few in the entire state to offer this procedure. Dr. Ceydeli also has Northwest Floridas most advanced Lumenis skin resurfacing laser. This unique fractional CO2 laser, unlike the Fraxel laser, has the advanced technology to treat deep acne and surgical scars by stimulating new collagen formation, along with its standard use for wrinkles and brown age spots on the skin.These innovative procedures and techniques are only few of the many services offered here at Plastic Surgery Institute & Spa. A picture is worth a thousand words, so we invite you to visit our before and after gallery and judge for yourself.

name: Pleasant Ridge Internal Medicine
bio: Dr. Theresa Stretch is Board Certified in Internal Medicine. She was born and raised in Texas and is a magna cum laude graduate of Incarnate Word College in San Antonio where she earned a B.S. in Biology.  She achieved her medical degree at the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, Texas. Following medical school Dr. Stretch completed an internship in Preliminary Medicine at John Sealy Hospital, Galveston. Her education was completed with an Internal Medicine Residency at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital in Dallas.Dr. Stretch lives in Dalworthington Gardens with her husband and children. She is the founder of Pleasant Ridge Internal Medicine. She built her practice with a specific vision, designing everything from the layout of the building to the interior with her patients care and comfort in mind. Dr. Stretch is a member of the American College of Physicians, The Texas Medical Association, and the Tarrant County Medical Society.

name: Pleasant Ridge Internal Medicine
bio: Marie T. Murphy, CNM was born and raised in Ireland. After receiving her RN license she moved to Scotland where she graduated in 1983 as a Midwife. Marie used her education to pursue her love of travel, first practicing Midwifery in Abu Dhabi, then in London, UK, Perth, Australia and in Saudi Arabia. For Marie working in such diverse areas of the world helped enrich her understanding and build a respect for the cultural traditions of women around the world.Marie is a very unique person; her professional and personal life experiences have given her a wonderful ability to relate to women in every stage of their lives. She has worked in private practice since 1997. In 2000, she joined Dr. Patrick Allen in his OB\/GYN practice located in North Richland Hills and Fort Worth.Being a Certified Nurses Midwife, Marie provides all aspects of in office gynecological and prenatal care with special emphasis on patient education, health and wellness promotion and disease prevention.

bio: Dr. Alvarado has maintained a private OB\/GYN practice in Bayamon, PR since 1997.  Previously worked in a multispecialty practice in Lake City Fl. Simultaneously has been the legal advisor for Health Law and Medico Legal Affairs to the Speaker of the House of Representatives of the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, as well as for the Municipal Legislatures of Catao and Toa Alta.Worked as Administrative Law Judge at the Puerto Rico Board for Medical Examiners dealing with disciplinary actions and Puerto Rico Emergency Management Agency for human resources disciplinary actions. bio: At Premier Obstetrics and Gynecology, Dr. John van Wert is a leading OB\/GYN, serving patients in and around the Greater Metro Orlando area in their Maitland, Florida offices. Dr. van Wert is a board certified obstetrician and gynecologist who has been practicing for over 28 years. He provides services such as bioidentical hormone replacement, menopause management, vaginal surgery and rejuvenation, and robotic hysterectomies in addition to standard gynecology services.Dr. van Wert obtained his undergraduate degree at Duke University in North Carolina, his medical degree from Vanderbilt University Medical School in Tennessee and residency at the University of Florida in Gainesville. Dr. van Wert excels in gynecologic surgery, especially laparoscopic surgery and robotic hysterectomies. He has been named as one of Central Floridas Top Doctors multiple times. Dr. van Wert is a long-standing board certified member of The American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is also a member of the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery and the American Association of Cosmetic Gynecologists.Dr. van Wert is married to Dr. Anne K. van Wert of Nemours Childrens Primary Care in Maitland and has two children. Both Christopher and Alexandra attended Duke University. Dr. van Wert enjoys multiple outdoor sports including cycling, skiing (snow and water) and sailing, but also loves cooking dinner for his family on a frequent basis.Dr. van Wert also pursues cosmetic procedures as well. Dr. van Wert has been extensively trained in VASER LipoSelection, Fraxel Laser and Intense Pulsed Light therapies, Non-invasive UltraShape fat removal, and injectables such as Botox, Dysport, Juvederm, Restylane, and Perlane. He continues to have a very active Gynecology and Surgery career and welcomes all new patients to Premier, where our providers strive to care for patients in the most technologically advanced, safest and comfortable environment available while maintaining the highest level of professional ethics and expertise.

name: Premier Pain Treatment Institute
bio: Courtney Guilfoyle FNP-C, earned her Bachelors of Science in Nursing from the University of Kentucky in 2010.  She began her career at Good Samaritan Hospital in Cincinnati, where she practiced for seven years on a post-surgical unit. She then went on to obtain her family nurse practitioner license from the University of Cincinnati, and is board certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. She currently specializes in chronic pain management at Premier Pain Treatment Institute in Mason, Ohio.  As a healthcare provider in this field, Courtney strives to provide patients with a variety of pharmacologic and interventional options to achieve optimal relief.  Her overall goal is to restore quality of life for these individuals. Courtneys professional memberships include AANP, and she spends her free time as a Beautycounter consultant educating consumers on safety in the personal care industry, and advocating for safer health protective laws.  She can also be found spending time with her husband and two young children.

He received his Fellowship training at the world-renowned Miami Cardiac & Vascular Institute, which is one of the most prestigious Fellowship training programs available for vascular and interventional radiology. He has more than 15 years of experience in interventional radiology and specializes in vascular and pain intervention procedures. His extensive training and experience make him an expert in minimally invasive procedures for treating varicose veins and acute\/chronic pain.

Holly has lived in Northern Colorado for 19 years and enjoys mountain biking and spending time with her two children and golden retriever.

name: Premier Women's Healthcare
bio: Dr. Dominique Smith is the medical director of Premier Womens Healthcare in Lithonia, GA.  Premier Womens healthcare & Aesthetics provides state of the art gynecologic, holistic and aesthetics care for women.  As a part of caring for her female patients treating the needs of her partner is also important which is why Dr. Smith also chose to become certified to treat male testosterone deficiency.Dr. Smith received her medical degree from Washington University School of Medicine in St. Louis, MO and completed her obstetrics and gynecology residency at Cook County Hospital in Chicago, IL. She is a member of such notable medical associations as the National Medical Association, Georgia OB\/GYN Society and AMA (Atlanta Medical Association) to name a few.  She is board certified in OB\/GYN and Integrative holistic medicine. With skill and compassion, Dr. Smith treats her patients with a comprehensive approach, taking care to listen to their individual concerns and providing them with a specific customized solution. Her approachable demeanor puts her patients at ease and her expertise on holistic medicines ensures excellent results.  Dr. Smith believes the best thing about being a doctor is helping people be healthy and beautiful  both inside and out.

name: Premier Women's Healthcare
bio: Treecie Miller is a womens health nurse practitioner, board certified in womens health and provides women-centered healthcare to female patients. She completed her B.S. degree in nursing at Middle Tennessee State University at Murfreesboro, TN then completed her masters at Vanderbilt University School of Nursing at Nashville, TN.  Treecie is currently a nurse practitioner at Premier Womens Healthcare. Treecie has a unique combination of strong nursing skills and strives to provide the best health care possible. She believes in building a long lasting and trusting relationship with her patient. She seeks to acquire a comprehensive evaluation of every patient by taking time to listen and understand their particular needs.

name: Premiere Weight Loss Center
bio: A native of Louisiana, Ms. Bennington received her bachelor's degree in nursing from the University of Louisiana at Monroe in 2006. Following several years practicing at Arlington Memorial Hospital, in the cardiovascular intensive care unit, Vanessa pursued her master's degree in nursing at University of Texas, Arlington, graduating in December 2010.She completed the family nurse practitioner and board certification examination through the nationally renowned American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC), a subsidiary of the American Nurses Association (ANA), receiving her Advanced Registered Nurse Practitioner designation (ARNP) in the spring of 2011.In practice for over nine years, Vanessa has applied her clinical knowledge and skills to helping men and women look and feel their best. She has mastered the application of many well-known dermal fillers and neuromodulators such as Botox, Juvederm, Radiesse, Artefill, Restylane and Voluma, used to soften fine lines, control wrinkles and enhance a youthful appearance. Additionally, Vanessa is skilled in a number of laser procedures, including laser hair removal, non-ablative skin resurfacing and IPL hyperpigmentation treatments for melasma and brown spots.For the last five years, Vanessa has focused her growing practice on the use of bio-identical hormone therapy (testosterone, estrogen and progesterone) to help patients regain a healthy hormone balance, improve energy and libido and decrease fatigue and depression. Evaluating all aspects of each patient's lab work, nutrition and adrenal issues, Vanessa develops a personalized, comprehensive plan to address their unique issues and needs.On a personal level, Vanessa received her bachelor's degree in exercise and health science from Louisiana Tech University, and enjoys promoting healthy living and fitness as a hobby. She and her husband own and operate Seward CrossFit Gym, in Sarasota, where she teaches fitness classes, and participates in CrossFit competiti

Dr. Simmons is a member of the American College of Obstetrics & Gynecology. His special interests are  Bioidentical hormonal treatment for both men & women. name: Prestige Medical Rejuvenation Center
bio: Dr. Jackson is a full-time practicing Emergency Medicine Physician that is board certified by the American Board of Emergency Medicine.  He trained in the military at Darnall Army Community Hospital, Fort Hood, Texas.  He completed his residency in 1997 and spent a total of 11 years on active duty in the Army deploying to both Bosnia and Iraq.  After separating from the Army in 2005, he worked at the University of Nebraska Medical Center's busy urban ED in Omaha, NE until 2009.  Since 2009, he has been working at the two Bryan Health Hospital ED's in Lincoln, NE.  He has a special interest in anti-aging medicine and men's sexual health. He owns and operates Prestige Medical Rejuvenation Center in Omaha, NE.  This clinic specializes in preventative medicine using bio-identical hormone therapy for both men and women as well as treatment for men's sexual issues including erectile dysfunction and premature ejaculation.   The goal at Prestige Medical Rejuvenation Center is to help our patients be happier and live healthier.

Dr. Evans is also an Associate Clinical Professor at the University of Texas, Health Science Center, Southwestern Medical School, Dallas. He is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: Preventive Medicine Center
bio: David M. Odom, MD, is Board Certified by the American Board of Anti-Aging & Regenerative Medicine and fellowship trained in stem cell medicine by the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine.  Dr. Odom is also a member of the Obesity Medicine Association and practices bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, weight management medicine, lifestyle coaching and stem cell medicine. Dr. Odom received his medical degree from Baylor College of Medicine, Houston and has been in practice for 46 years.  He had anesthesiology residency training at Los Angeles County  USC Medical Center and Childrens Hospital, Los Angeles.  He is board certified in anesthesiology, but gave up operating room work 22 years ago in order to devote his practice to age management and preventive medicine.  Dr. Odoms professional interest is restoration and maintenance of health for middle-aged and older men and women utilizing the newest and most natural techniques.

name: Primary Care and Wellness Center of Florida
bio: Dr. Beethoven Ruedas is a caring and diligent primary care doctor serving the community of Jacksonville, FL. Dr. Ruedas earned his medical degree from the Cebu Institute of Medicine in Philippines. He then moved to the United States to complete his residency at Illinois Masonic Medical Center in Chicago.Dr. Ruedas has held positions at the Primary Care and Wellness Center of Florida, St. Johns Medical Center, and Alaric Health Beauty and Wellness. He also served the military as a veteran at Desert Storm Gulf War and as a lieutenant and captain at the U.S. Navy Medical Corp. He retired in 1997. Dr. Ruedas was affiliated with St. Vincent Medical Center ambulatory primary care and urgent care and Baptist Ambulatory Care and Occupational Health. He is a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians, the Florida Academy of Family Physicians, the Military Officers Association, and the Philippine Medical Society of Northeast Florida. Dr. Ruedas is deeply committed to the well-being of his patients. He takes a thorough and precise approach to his consultations to ensure that he is consistently giving accurate diagnoses. He conducts his appointments with the personalized care and attention that he would expect for his own family.

Dr. Sharp has developed and is currently still enrolling patients in his membership based practice, Doctors for Health, with an emphasis on personalized healthcare, advanced lab testing, and increased availability. Dr. Sharp is certified by Age Management Medical Group (AMMG), which focuses on a preventative approach to medicine. Thru Dr. Sharps certification, he is able to preserve quality of life by optimizing human function thru hormone replacement and reducing the aging process caused by chronic disease. Dr. Sharp also treats diagnoses including low back, neck, and hip related pains by using musculoskeletal manipulation, as an alternative or additional treatment plan to pain medications.

name: Pro Health Services
bio: A Central Ohio native and a Board-Certified Family, Obesity and Addictionologist Physician, Dr. Angel Alexander specializes in everything from obesity to opiate dependency.Earning a Bachelor of Science from The Ohio State University and a Medical Degree from the University of Cincinnati College of Medicine, Dr. Alexander completed her residency at Mount Carmel Medical Center.  Serving as a Family Physician for over 14 years, Dr. Alexander provides medical care for the entire family including preventative care such as physicals, pap smears and acute care for infections. Dr. Alexander also manages chronic conditions such as high blood pressure, diabetes, high cholesterol and obesity.  In addition, Dr. Alexander is a certified BioTe Physician specializing in balancing hormones.Providing ALCAT Food Sensitivity Test to detect and reduce food sensitivities and MedGem to measure metabolism, Dr. Alexander's  goal is to enhance your health and wellness to improve your quality of life.

name: ProCare Medical Center
bio: Dr. Clark is a national lecturer on many topics ranging from aerovac of battlefield wounds to workplace exposure to contaminants.  We are very happy to have her on-board with Pro-Care Medical Center.  When she is not in the office, Dr. Clark constantly works with horses.  In fact, she regularly states that she works for horses.  Literally, she has 10 horses to feed and shelter!  We all wish her luck!

name: ProCare Medical Center
bio: Dr. Daniel L. Rasor of Pro-Care Medical Center in Austin, Texas is a board certified primary care physician who has been serving patients of all ages in South Austin for over two decades. Committed to providing individualized, top quality care, Dr. Rasor offers a full scope of preventative and treatment services, including: annual checkups for child and adults, well-woman exams, immunizations, management of chronic illnesses (sleep apnea, hypertension, diabetes, and asthma, etc.), and a wide array of screening tests (hypertension, diabetes, high cholesterol, and cervical cancer, etc.).He is widely praised by patients for his personable bedside manner and willingness to answer questions in detail, as well as, his top-notch skills.Dr. Rasor received his undergraduate degree from the University of Texas-Austin, then went on to earn his medical degree at the Medical School at Universidad Autonoma de Guadalajara in Guadalajara, Mexico. He completed his residency in family practice at Poly Clinic in Harrisburg, PA.In his free time, Dr. Rasor enjoys Austins live music scene, UT football, boating, cycling and spending time with his children.

name: ProCare Medical Center
bio: Mathew Mitchell is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner whose academic background includes a Bachelor of Arts and Science from Texas Tech University (2005), as well as a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Hardin-Simmons University (2009). He received his Masters of Science in Nursing and Family Nurse Practitioners license from Samford University in 2011 with honors. Mathew has worked in all aspects of patient care including critical care, emergency medicine, orthopedic medicine, and pain management. He is a member of Sigma Theta Tau Honor Society and American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.

name: ProCare Medical Center
bio: Bindu Sam FNP was born and raised in the garden city of India, Bangalore. She graduated with a family Nurse Practitioner degree from Texas Tech University Health Science Center, Lubbock Texas. Her undergraduate education was completed at Government College of Nursing, Bangalore, India. She has seventeen years of experience in nursing, serving under various capacities including general medicine, trauma, critical care and pediatrics. She assumed the position of Assistant lecturer in nursing from 1999 to 2001 in the school of nursing department of one of the prestigious deemed universities of India MAHE, Manipal. Following this, she traveled along with her husband to New Zealand and worked for Auckland District Health Board. She is a resident of San Antonio since 2006 along with her husband and two children. Majority of her clinical experience during her education was at the family practice clinic of UTHSCSA in San Antonio where she catered to patients from all walks of life. To add to her accomplishments, she is nationally certified in pediatric nursing, can speak four Indian languages and is a great advocate of evidence based comprehensive health Care.She likes to play guitar and also belongs to a mission oriented family. So during her leisure gets involved in church activities and singing.

name: Progressive Medical Center
bio: Lorena Torres is a nurse practitioner board certified by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners in family medicine. She received her Masters of Science in Nursing at Georgia State University.  Lorena has a vast experience ranging from bedside nursing to clinical instructor.  Her experience includes being a board certified emergency room nurse at Piedmont Hospital for 5 years.  She also has experience in plastic surgery working along the nations best craniofacial and cosmetic plastic surgeons. During her graduate studies, she was a graduate teacher assistant at Georgia State University. After completion of her Masters degree, she stayed on board her Alma Mater as a Clinical Instructor for the undergraduate nursing students.  Her nurse practitioner experience includes primary care, infectious disease and currently practices integrative and functional medicine in Atlanta, GA.  Lorena is also an experienced facial injector working with Botox and platelet rich plasma (PRP).  Lorenas other training includes oxidative therapies, including joint injections. As a nurse practitioner, Lorena enjoys getting to know her patients so that healing can take place in a holistic manner. She is a Colorado native who loves animals and the outdoors.  She currently resides in downtown Atlanta with her husband.  Past time activities include hiking, watching movies, gardening, and traveling.  She is also a passionate Door Holder (volunteer) for Passion City Church in Atlanta, GA.

name: ProMD Health
bio: The founder of ProMD Health, George Gavrila is a native of the Greater Baltimore area and has spent time studying medicine, primary care, functional medicine, aesthetic medicine, and integrative medicine.Dr. Gavrila completed his residency at the University of Maryland and served as a Fellow at the Center of Integrative Medicine at the University of Maryland School of Medicine. Dr. Gavrila developed an interest in integrative and anti-aging medicine after recognizing many of the present medical systems' shortcomings. Patients appreciate a professional and confidential environment, as well as prompt appointments with a skilled and compassionate doctor. Dr. Gavrila is a member of AMMG (Age Management Medicine Group); A4M (American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine); AAFE (American Academy of Facial Esthetics); Forever Health; IFM (Institute for Functional Medicine); AAAM (American Academy of Aesthetic Medicine); ASLMS (American Society for Laser Medicine & Surgery).

name: ProMD Health
bio: Amy is a Biote trained practitioner who believes with Biote hormone optimization, you can feel as amazing on the inside as you look on the outside.

name: ProMD Health
bio: My name is Janette Roderick. I am a BioTE Certified Practitioner practicing in Annapolis, MD and Washington, DC. Janette is a Physician Assistant board certified by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants and a Fellow member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants. She graduated in 2013 from the George Washington University School of Medicine with a Masters in Health Sciences and certificate in Physician Assistant studies. There, Janette completed the Advanced Surgical program and additional training in Plastic Surgery, Trauma Surgery, and Wound Care. Her career began in Emergency Medicine for the George Washington University Hospital where she worked for several years before transitioning to cosmetic dermatology and anti-aging with ProMD Health. As a member of ProMD Health, Janette focuses on helping patients look and feel their best through facial rejuvenation, hair restoration, skin treatments, and hormone optimization. She began practicing bio-identical hormone optimization and pellet therapy to help fight the metabolic and hormonal imbalances that come with aging and decrease ones quality of life. My goal is to increase vitality and self-esteem in my patients. I think bio-identical hormone replacement and nutraceutical therapy is extremely beneficial to patients as it helps to decrease symptoms of menopause, decrease inflammation that can accelerate aging, increase energy, increase libido, and increase overall sense of wellbeing. Aside from practicing medicine, Janette enjoys being outdoors, boating, dancing, and interior design. She currently resides in Arlington, Virginia with her husband Bo and their cat Poose.
