name: Promise Land Women's Center OBGYN
bio: Hyacinth Dennis-Crooks is a Family Nurse Practitioner . A native of Jamaica W.I She graduated with her Baccalaureate of science degree from The College of Mount Saint Vincent in New York State where she was a member of The International Nursing Honor Society , Sigma Theta Tau. She obtain a Masters of Science Degree in Nursing from Kennesaw State University in 2004 and was Board certify as a Family Nurse Practitioner in 2005.

name: Providence Medical Institute - Torrance OBGYN
bio: Dr Madati grew up in Jackson, Mississippi, by her father, who was a cardiovascular and thoracic surgeon, inspired her to become a compassionate physician. Dr Madati spent her high school summers working at my father's office. She enjoyed listening to patients, learning about their stories, and tackling their health concerns. These experiences were the seeds of my love for medicine. Now, she is able to be a part of the most amazing stories of women's lives like child birth. As an obstetrician\/gynecologist, Dr Madati aspires to bring a spirit of trust, detail and kindness to each story. Dr Madati and her husband have one daughter . Outside of medicine, she enjoys cooking, scrapbooking, running and traveling across the world.

name: Pure Center of Health
bio: Dee is a Family Nurse Practitioner with 40 years of experience in the Medical and Alternative Health fields. She received her BSN and MSN from Colorado University Health Sciences Center. Dee has received advanced training in Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy (BHRT) and currently is a Certified Practitioner with BioTE Medical in the North Denver metro area. This therapy is very successful at treating symptoms of hormone decline for both women and men. She has also been trained in Homeopathy by Andre Saine since 1998. For the Pure Center, she offers a unique combination of both traditional and alternative\/natural methods and treatments focusing on each patients overall Health, Wellness and Prevention. Dee would be happy to meet with you to talk about strategies for long term health.

name: Pure Radiance Laser Retreat
bio: Dr. Stewart grew up in San Antonio, Texas where he graduated from Churchill High School. After graduating with a Bachelor of Science in Biology from Texas A&M University, he went to Baylor College of Medicine in Houston where he did biochemical research for two years. Next, he attended University of Texas Health Science Center Medical School. His internship and residency were completed in 1987 at the Dallas Southwestern Family Practice Program in Wichita Falls, TX. Since completing his residency, Dr. Stewart has practiced Emergency Medicine in Tyler, TX for over 20 years. He has served on multiple committees and boards including Smith County Medical Association. His memberships include Fellow of the American Academy of Family Physicians, American Society for Laser Medicine and American Society for Photodynamic Therapy. His interest and passion for healthier lifestyles influenced his desire to pursue additional training in the field of hormone therapy and aesthetic medicine. He opened Pure Radiance Med Spa in Tyler in 2006.

name: Purtiy Medical Spa
bio: My name is Dr. Fadi Alhafez and I am extremely committed to my clients well being and satisfaction. I am devoted to helping them to reach their greatest physical potential which will in turn help them with their level of confidence.   I did my clinical training at East Carolina University in Greenville, NC. Later, I finished my residency in internal medicine at Rosalind Franklin University in Chicago, IL. I have a love of learning and I am eager to grow educationally and proffessionaly. Thus, I pursued an MBA in Health Care Management at Loyola University in Chicago, IL.I have over 12 years postgraduate experience in outpatient and inpatient care. Furthermore, I am currently employed at St Peter Hospital in Olympia .I decided to further my education and knowledge in the cosmetic industry by attending several conferences and trainings in injections, botox, fillers and laser. I would love the opportunity to demonstrate my skills and help my clients reach the best version of themselves.

name: Purtiy Medical Spa
bio: Christi Payne is a native from Salt Lake City, Utah. She decided early on that she wanted to care for others. She attended the University of Utah where she received her Bachelors degree in nursing with a minor in anthropology. After working more than ten years in the intensive care unit she moved to Texas where she obtained her Masters degree in family practice from Texas A&M Corpus Christi. She then attended Seattle University where she obtained her post masters certification in acute care. She has been working in the sub acute setting as a nurse practitioner. Her hobbies include hiking, skiing, and enjoying the outdoors.

name: Quality of Life Medical & Research Center
bio: Dr. McGettigan is the founder and driving force behind Qualify of Life Medical Center (QLMC) and Quality of Life Medical & Research Center (QLMRC), and a graduate of Emory Medical School in Atlanta, Georgia. After moving to Tucson, Dr. McGettigan attended the University of Arizona, where he trained as a General Surgeon before specializing in Emergency Medicine. Later, at Thomas Davis Medical Center, Dr. McGettigan was one of the first doctors added to the staff, working in the Urgent Care clinic.It was in 2000 that Dr. McGettigan branched off into private practice and launched QLMC, specializing in Mens Health and General Medicine. Then, in 2001, Dr. McGettigan attained synergy by adding a research division  QLMRC  to his medical practice.QLMRC has grown into a regional leader in the pioneering of new drugs and medical procedures. Over the years, pharmaceutical companies including Amgen, Eli Lilly, GSK, Merck, Pfizer, Novartis, Roche, and Baxter have relied on QLMRC, the cutting-edge role it plays in the world of medicine, and its advances in the field of life-changing drugs, vaccines, and devices.Dr. McGettigan specializes In:General medical careEmergency medical servicesHormone therapy for men and womenMedical researchGynecological examsDr. McGettigan is a leader in the medical pharmaceutical research industry. He has been a Principal Investigator in the following clinical research fields:Diabetic careHypertensionErectile dysfunctionTestosterone replacementSoft-tissue injuriesMigrainesVaccines (influenza, herpes)Weight-loss therapies and drugsOsteoarthritis\/chronic pain

name: Quality of Life Medical & Research Center
bio: John vonKersburg PA-C is a native of Durango, Colorado and has been in Tucson for the past 12 years. John graduated Magna Cum Laude from Grand College University in human biology and exercise physiology. John received his degree as a physicians assistant from the Arizona School of Health Sciences.In his years of medical practice John has taken a holistic approach to treating patients symptoms and working to counsel the patient to get back to their optimum health. John has an extensive background in internal medicine.Johns passion in medicine circles around the field of bariatric medicine and the field of medically supervised weight loss.

name: Questcare Medical Clinic
bio: Dr. Matthew Opalach is an experienced family medicine physician in Arlington who has provided excellent care in both primary care and urgent care settings. He earned his medical degree from the University of North Texas Health Science Center and completed Family Medicine residency at Plaza Medical Center of Fort Worth.He provides comprehensive primary care services to patients of all ages. A native of the Dallas-Fort Worth area, Dr. Opalach enjoys staying physically active, practicing the sport of jiu-jitsu, studying philosophy, and spending time with his wife and children.Family Medicine ResidencyPlaza Medical Center of Fort Worth, Fort Worth, TexasMedical SchoolUniversity of North Texas Health Science Center, Fort Worth, TexasArlington Family MedicineDr. Opalach currently provides medical care at the Questcare Medical Clinic in Arlington, TX. Our medical clinic provides care for a wide range of chronic and acute medical conditions. Our medical staff has the experience and expertise to provide advanced medical care for your medical needs.

name: Questcare Medical Clinic
bio: Jay Pribble, MPAS, PA-C, is a Physician Assistant certified by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants. Jay grew up in the Northwestern United States. He then moved to Denver and received his undergraduate degrees from the University of Colorado and from Metro State University of Denver. After living in Denver for several years, Jay relocated to the DFW area. Jay provides care for patients of all ages.  He enjoys treating patients with chronicdiseases and working with pediatric patients. Jay is skilled in acute and chronic disease management as well as in-office procedures. In his free time, Jay enjoys all sports, exercising, learning about wines and spending time with his wife and dogs.EducationUniversity of North Texas Health Science Center, Fort Worth, Texas Arlington Family MedicineJay Pribble currently provides medical care at the Questcare Medical Clinic in Arlington, TX. Our medical clinic provides care for a wide range of chronic and acute medical conditions. Our medical staff has the experience and expertise to provide advanced medical care for your medical needs.

name: Questcare Medical Clinic
bio: Dr. Nilda Lopez is a Family Medicine physician with a kind and caring manner. A long-time resident of North Texas, she earned her medical degree from University of Texas Medical Branch at Galveston and gained family medicine training and experience during her residency at John Peter Smith Hospital. She has additional training for the care of patients of advanced age and completed fellowship in Geriatric Medicine at John Peter Smith Hospital.She provides comprehensive primary care, withShe provides comprehensive primary care, with particular interest in geriatric medicine, pediatrics, and tropical medicine. She most enjoys the ability to care for the whole family at all stages of life. Dr. Lopez enjoys mission work, poetry, singing, traveling, being involved with her church and spending time with her family.

name: Questcare Medical Clinic
bio: Mamta Sigdel is a board-certified family practice nurse. She serves as a family practitioner for Dallas-based Questcare clinics providing care for all ages.Mamta has more than 10 years of experience working in various roles within the healthcare industry. She has worked with patient of all ages, but has a strong interest adult and geriatric patients.Mamtas decade of experience working with a wide range of patients shapes her holistic philosophy. Mamta believes clinicians should consider more than just the patients superficial condition when treating them, but also weigh the patients emotional and environmental factors when assessing their medical needs.When not practicing medicine, Mamta enjoys traveling and spending time with family. Mamta is originally from Nepal. She moved to Texas to pursue her undergraduate degree.

name: Questcare Medical Clinic at Burleson
bio: Terri Speck, MSN, APRN, FNP-C, is a Family Nurse Practitioner certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners (AANP). Terri was raised in Burleson, Texas and loves helping patients and raising her family in her own hometown.Terri provides excellent primary care and minor emergency care to her patients. She has particular interest in disease prevention and wellness. She is compassionate and skilled, with nearly two decades of experience as an oncology nurse serving patients with cancer. She enjoys gardening, reading and cooking with her family and friends.
